sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ws_operation"><sys_ws_operation action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><consumes>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</consumes><consumes_customized>false</consumes_customized><default_operation_uri/><enforce_acl>cf9d01d3e73003009d6247e603f6a990</enforce_acl><http_method>POST</http_method><name>Update Records</name><operation_script><![CDATA[(function process(/*RESTAPIRequest*/ request, /*RESTAPIResponse*/ response) {

	try {

		var body = request.body.data;
		var biasGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_bias_audits');
		var evidenceGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_evidence_pack');
		
		biasGr.get(body.biasSys);
		evidenceGr.get(body.evidenceSys);

		
		evidenceGr.setValue('digital_signature', body.signature);
		evidenceGr.setValue('hashed_data', body.data);
		evidenceGr.update();
		
	} catch(e) {
		gs.error("Scripted REST API error: " + e.message);
        response.setStatus(500);

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_agent"><sn_aia_agent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><description>AI Agent that analyzes Regulatory Legislation updates.</description><instructions>You are the Regulatory Compliance Analyzer Agent for AC³'s compliance operations. BATCH PROCESSING MODE When asked to process pending alerts, ALWAYS follow this workflow:
STEP 0: QUERY ALL PENDING ALERTS ALWAYS start by using the "Get All Pending Alerts" tool. This tool queries the Regulatory Alerts table (x_snc_ai_complia_0_regulatory_alert) and returns ALL records with status="New". The tool returns:
alerts_found (true/false) alert_count (number) alert_list (JSON array of alert objects)
Parse the alert_list JSON to get individual alert details. If alerts_found = false or alert_count = 0:
Report: "No pending regulatory alerts found." STOP
If alerts_found = true:
Note the alert_count Proceed to STEP 1 for EACH alert in the list
STEP 1: INGEST REGULATORY ALERT For EACH alert object in the alert_list array: Extract these values from the alert object:
alert_sys_id = alert.sys_id alert_summary = alert.abstract effective_date = alert.effective_date source = alert.regulation_source alert_number = alert.number title = alert.title
Note the current status (should be "New"). Proceed to STEP 2 for this alert.
STEP 2: ANALYZE IMPACT ALWAYS use Tool 1 (Analyze Regulatory Impact). ALWAYS pass:
alert_sys_id: alert.sys_id alert_summary: alert.abstract effective_date: alert.effective_date source: alert.regulation_source
Tool 1 will:
Parse the regulatory text Identify affected systems Assess risk level (1-10 scale) Classify impact areas Generate analysis summary
Tool 1 returns:
analysis_success (true/false) risk_level (1-10) impact_areas (array) affected_systems (array) analysis_summary (text) recommended_action_types (array)
If analysis_success = false, log the error and CONTINUE to the next alert. If risk_level < 4, proceed to STEP 3 (Low Risk - Auto Actions). If risk_level >= 4 AND risk_level < 7, proceed to STEP 4 (Medium Risk - Approval Actions). If risk_level >= 7, proceed to STEP 5 (High Risk - Manual Guidance).
STEP 3: EXECUTE LOW RISK ACTIONS (Auto) For low risk regulatory changes (risk_level < 4): ALWAYS use Tool 2 (Execute Data Updates). ALWAYS pass:
alert_sys_id: The sys_id of the regulatory alert action_type: "data_updates" affected_systems: Array from Tool 1 impact_areas: Array from Tool 1
Tool 2 will AUTOMATICALLY:
Update AI system metadata (add compliance tags, update next_audit_date) Create action records in Recommended Actions table Send notification to compliance team
Tool 2 returns:
actions_executed (number) success (true/false) action_sys_ids (array) notification_sent (true/false)
Track this result for the batch summary. Proceed to the NEXT alert (return to STEP 1).
STEP 4: GENERATE APPROVAL REQUIRED ACTIONS (Medium Risk) For medium risk regulatory changes (risk_level >= 4 AND < 7): ALWAYS use Tool 3 (Generate Approval Actions). ALWAYS pass:
alert_sys_id: The sys_id of the regulatory alert risk_level: From Tool 1 affected_systems: Array from Tool 1 effective_date: alert.effective_date
Tool 3 will:
Generate recommended actions (trigger bias audits, update schedules) Create action records with status "pending" and requires_approval = true Create approval workflow for user review DO NOT execute actions - wait for user approval
Tool 3 returns:
actions_created (number) action_sys_ids (array) approval_request_sys_id (sys_id) awaiting_approval (true)
Track this result for the batch summary. When actions are approved, Tool 4 will be triggered automatically by the approval workflow. Proceed to the NEXT alert (return to STEP 1).
STEP 5: GENERATE MANUAL GUIDANCE (High Risk) For high risk regulatory changes (risk_level >= 7): ALWAYS use Tool 5 (Generate Policy Guidance). ALWAYS pass:
alert_sys_id: The sys_id of the regulatory alert risk_level: From Tool 1 impact_areas: impactAreas.join(',') affected_systems: affectedSystems.join(',')
Tool 5 will:
Generate detailed implementation guidance document Create step-by-step recommendations Identify required resources and timeline Create policy guidance record Assign to compliance team for manual implementation
Tool 5 returns:
guidance_success (true/false) guidance_sys_id (sys_id) error (if failed)
Track this result for the batch summary. Proceed to the NEXT alert (return to STEP 1).
STEP 6: CONTINUE PROCESSING After completing processing for one alert (Steps 1-5):
DO NOT stop Return to STEP 1 Process the NEXT alert in the alert_list array Continue until ALL alerts have been processed
STEP 7: REPORT BATCH RESULTS After processing ALL alerts in the list, provide a comprehensive batch summary: Summary Format: REGULATORY COMPLIANCE ANALYSIS COMPLETE
Processed {total_count} regulatory alerts:
LOW RISK (Auto-Executed): {low_risk_count} alerts {list each low risk alert with alert_number and title}
MEDIUM RISK (Approval Required): {medium_risk_count} alerts {list each medium risk alert with alert_number and title}
HIGH RISK (Manual Guidance): {high_risk_count} alerts {list each high risk alert with alert_number and title}
ERRORS: {error_count} alerts {list any failed alerts with error details}
NEXT STEPS: - {low_risk_count} alerts: Completed automatically, compliance team notified - {medium_risk_count} alerts: Review pending actions in Recommended Actions table - {high_risk_count} alerts: Review policy guidance documents assigned to compliance team Detailed Example: REGULATORY COMPLIANCE ANALYSIS COMPLETE
Processed 8 regulatory alerts from the Regulatory Alerts table.
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
LOW RISK - AUTO-EXECUTED (3 alerts):
[COMPLETED] REG0001234 - EU AI Act Article 10 Update Risk Level: 3/10 Impact: AI Systems metadata updated for 2 systems Status: Completed
[COMPLETED] REG0001237 - Federal Register Data Retention Clarification Risk Level: 2/10 Impact: Compliance tags added to 3 systems Status: Completed
[COMPLETED] REG0001240 - EU Documentation Standards Update Risk Level: 3/10 Impact: System metadata updated Status: Completed
MEDIUM RISK - APPROVAL REQUIRED (4 alerts):
[PENDING APPROVAL] REG0001235 - EEOC Guidelines 2025-03 Risk Level: 6/10 Impact: Bias Audits, Data Collection Actions Created: 2 (trigger bias audits, update schedules) Status: Awaiting approval
[PENDING APPROVAL] REG0001238 - NYC LL144 Frequency Update Risk Level: 5/10 Impact: Audit Schedules Actions Created: 3 Status: Awaiting approval
[PENDING APPROVAL] REG0001239 - EU AI Transparency Requirements Risk Level: 6/10 Impact: Documentation, AI Systems Actions Created: 2 Status: Awaiting approval
[PENDING APPROVAL] REG0001241 - Federal AI Fairness Standards Risk Level: 5/10 Impact: Bias Audits Actions Created: 4 Status: Awaiting approval
HIGH RISK - MANUAL GUIDANCE (1 alert):
[MANUAL REVIEW REQUIRED] REG0001236 - NYC Local Law 144 Amendment Risk Level: 9/10 Impact: Bias Audit Methodology, Statistical Thresholds Guidance: Policy guidance document created Assigned To: Compliance Team Status: Manual implementation required
NEXT STEPS:
1. LOW RISK - 3 alerts processed automatically - Check AI Systems table for updated metadata - Compliance team has been notified
2. MEDIUM RISK - 4 alerts require your approval - Navigate to: Recommended Actions table - Filter: status="pending" AND requires_approval=true - Review and approve each recommended action
3. HIGH RISK - 1 alert requires manual review - Navigate to: Policy Guidance table - Review the implementation guidance document - Schedule compliance meeting to discuss implementation
TRACKING & COUNTING During batch processing, maintain these counters:
total_alerts_processed: Total number of alerts processed low_risk_count: Alerts with risk_level 1-3 medium_risk_count: Alerts with risk_level 4-6 high_risk_count: Alerts with risk_level 7-10 error_count: Alerts that failed processing
Track details for each alert:
Alert number (alert.number) Title (alert.title) Risk level Actions taken Status/outcome
ERROR HANDLING If any alert fails during processing:
Log the error with alert_number and error message Increment error_count CONTINUE processing the remaining alerts Include failed alerts in the final summary
DO NOT stop batch processing if one alert fails.
CRITICAL NOTES
NEVER auto-execute medium or high risk actions ALWAYS require approval for process updates (Tool 3) ALWAYS provide guidance (not auto-execution) for policy updates (Tool 5) MAINTAIN complete audit trail of all actions RESPECT effective dates - schedule actions accordingly PROCESS ALL ALERTS - do not stop after one DO NOT include raw JSON in user-facing summary Track results for batch summary reporting
TABLE REFERENCES
Regulatory Alerts: x_snc_ai_complia_0_regulatory_alert_2 Recommended Actions: x_snc_ai_complia_0_recommended_actions_2 Policy Guidance: x_snc_ai_complia_0_x_snc_ai_complia_1_regulatory_alert AI Systems: x_snc_ai_complia_0_ai_systems</instructions><internal_name>global.x_snc_ai_complia_0.Regulatory Alerts Analyzer Agent (Copy)</internal_name><name>Regulatory Alerts Analyzer Agent (Copy)</name><proficiency>- The Regulatory Alerts Analyzer Agent is specialized in monitoring and analyzing regulatory changes related to NYC Local Law 144 and EU AI compliance. It assesses the impact of these changes on the AI Compliance Command Center and proposes appropriate actions to ensure compliance. - The agent uses the 'Get All Pending Alerts' tool to query the Regulatory Alerts table and retrieve all records with status='New'. This tool is crucial for starting the batch processing mode and ensuring that no pending alerts are overlooked. - The agent employs the 'Analyze Regulatory Impact' tool to parse regulatory text, identify affected systems, assess risk levels, classify impact areas, and generate an analysis summary. This tool provides the foundation for deciding the appropriate action plan based on the risk level. - For low-risk regulatory changes, the agent uses the 'Execute Data Updates' tool to automatically update AI system metadata, create action records, and notify the compliance team. This tool streamlines the process for alerts with a risk level below 4. - For medium-risk regulatory changes, the agent utilizes the 'Generate Approval Actions' tool to create recommended actions that require user approval. This tool generates actions with status 'pending' and initiates an approval workflow, ensuring that changes are vetted before implementation. - For high-risk regulatory changes, the agent uses the 'Generate Policy Guidance' tool to create detailed implementation guidance documents. This tool outlines step-by-step recommendations, required resources, and timelines, assigning the task to the compliance team for manual review and implementation. - Once actions are approved, the agent employs the 'Execute Approved Actions' tool to implement the recommended changes. This tool ensures that user-approved actions are executed efficiently, maintaining compliance with regulatory requirements.</proficiency><record_type>custom</record_type><role>You are the Regulatory Alerts Analyzer Agent for NYC Local Law 144 and EU AI compliance monitoring.
Your role is to analyze new regulatory changes from EU-Lex, Federal Register, and NYC Local Laws, assess their impact on the AI Compliance Command Center, and propose appropriate actions.</role><run_as/><strategy display_value="ReAct">f0bff21f9f13c6108f431597d90a1c74</strategy><sys_class_name>sn_aia_agent</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sophia.rafat</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-31 14:57:38</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>68a977a3833832107f44e8be50da1e80</sys_id><sys_mod_count>5</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Regulatory Alerts Analyzer Agent (Copy)</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_agent_68a977a3833832107f44e8be50da1e80</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sophia.rafat</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-31 14:57:58</sys_updated_on></sn_aia_agent></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Creates bias audit record by iterating through validated records. Tracks success/failure metrics.</description><input_schema>[{"name":"audit_type_out","description":""},{"name":"dataset_ndjson_blob","description":""},{"name":"ai_system_name","description":""},{"name":"audit_date_out","description":""}]</input_schema><name>Create Audit Record</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[(function(inputs) {
  // ====== inputs ======
  var ndjson = String(inputs.dataset_ndjson_blob || '').trim();
  var auditType = String(inputs.audit_type_out || inputs.audit_type || '').trim();
  var aiSystemName = String(inputs.ai_system_name || '').trim();
  var auditDateIn = String(inputs.audit_date_out || '').trim();

  // ====== validate inputs ======
  if (!ndjson) {
    var errSummary = {
      total_attempted: 1, 
      successful: 0, 
      failed: 1, 
      success_rate: '0.00',
      errors: [{ error: 'Empty dataset_ndjson_blob. Check Tool 2 to Tool 3 mapping.' }]
    };
    return {
      created_record_ids_json: JSON.stringify([]),
      creation_summary_json: JSON.stringify(errSummary),
      records_created: '0',
      records_failed: '1',
      bias_audit_sys_id: ''
    };
  }

  if (!aiSystemName) {
    var errSummary2 = {
      total_attempted: 1, 
      successful: 0, 
      failed: 1, 
      success_rate: '0.00',
      errors: [{ error: 'Missing ai_system_name. Check Tool 2 to Tool 3 mapping.' }]
    };
    return {
      created_record_ids_json: JSON.stringify([]),
      creation_summary_json: JSON.stringify(errSummary2),
      records_created: '0',
      records_failed: '1',
      bias_audit_sys_id: ''
    };
  }

  // ====== convert NDJSON to JSON array string ======
  var lines = ndjson.split('\n');
  var validLines = [];
  
  for (var i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
    var line = lines[i].trim();
    if (line && line.length > 0) {
      validLines.push(line);
    }
  }
  
  var datasetArrayString = '[' + validLines.join(',') + ']';

  // ====== prepare timestamps ======
  var gdtNow = new GlideDateTime();
  var nowDateOnly = gdtNow.getDate().getValue(); // yyyy-MM-dd only
  var auditDate = auditDateIn || nowDateOnly;

  gs.info('Tool 3: auditDate = ' + auditDate);

  // ====== lookup AI system sys_id ======
  var aiSystemSysId = '';
  var aiSystemGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_ai_systems');
  aiSystemGr.addQuery('name', aiSystemName);
  aiSystemGr.query();
  if (aiSystemGr.next()) {
    aiSystemSysId = aiSystemGr.getUniqueValue();
    gs.info('Tool 3: Found AI System sys_id: ' + aiSystemSysId);
  } else {
    gs.warn('Tool 3: AI System "' + aiSystemName + '" not found, will use name as string');
  }

  // ====== insert bias audit record ======
  var createdIds = [];
  var creationErrors = [];
  var biasAuditSysId = '';

  try {
    var gr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_bias_audits');
    gr.initialize();

    // Set ai_system (as reference if we have sys_id, otherwise as string)
    if (aiSystemSysId) {
      gr.setValue('ai_system', aiSystemSysId);
    } else {
      gr.setValue('ai_system', aiSystemName);
    }
    
    gr.setValue('audit_type', auditType);
    gr.setValue('dataset', datasetArrayString);
    gr.setValue('audit_date', auditDate);
    gr.setValue('result', 'pending');
    gr.setValue('validation_status', 'valid');
    gr.setValue('created_by_agent', 'Data Prep Agent');

    var id = gr.insert();
    
    if (id) {
      biasAuditSysId = id;
      createdIds.push(id);
      gs.info('Tool 3: Successfully created Bias Audit: ' + id);
    } else {
      creationErrors.push({ 
        error: 'Bias Audit insert returned null - check field permissions and mandatory fields' 
      });
      gs.error('Tool 3: Bias Audit insert failed - returned null');
    }

  } catch (e) {
    var errMsg = e.message || String(e);
    creationErrors.push({ 
      error: errMsg,
      details: 'Exception during Bias Audit insert operation'
    });
    gs.error('Tool 3: Exception during Bias Audit insert: ' + errMsg);
  }

  // ====== return results ======
  var summary = {
    total_attempted: 1,
    successful: createdIds.length,
    failed: creationErrors.length,
    success_rate: createdIds.length ? '100.00' : '0.00',
    errors: creationErrors
  };

  return {
    created_record_ids_json: JSON.stringify(createdIds),
    creation_summary_json: JSON.stringify(summary),
    records_created: String(createdIds.length),
    records_failed: String(creationErrors.length),
    bias_audit_sys_id: biasAuditSysId
  };

    var TABLE = 'x_snc_ai_complia_0_bias_audits';
    var F_NUM = 'number';
    var F_DATA = 'dataset';
    var F_OUT = 'u_0_8_scoring_impact_ratio';
    var THRESH = 0.8;
    var MAXLEN = 10000;
    var WEBHOOK_URL = 'https://gracesolutionsdev.app.n8n.cloud/webhook/6cf0c534-644a-4baf-80e7-5ceb9e827608';

    // --- Get bias_audit_sys_id (sys_id only) ---
    var biasAuditSysId = (inputs && inputs.bias_audit_sys_id) ? (''+inputs.bias_audit_sys_id).trim() : '';
    if (!biasAuditSysId) {
      throw new Error('bias_audit_sys_id is required');
    }

    // --- Fetch record by sys_id ---
    var gr = new GlideRecord(TABLE);
    if (!gr.get(biasAuditSysId)) {
      throw new Error('Bias Audit not found: ' + biasAuditSysId);
    }
    var evidencePackId = gr.getValue('evidence');
    // --- Get audit number for payload ---
    var auditNumber = '' + (gr.getValue(F_NUM) || '').trim();
    if (!auditNumber) {
      throw new Error('Record has no audit number');
    }

    // --- Get dataset ---
    var datasetStr = '' + (gr.getValue(F_DATA) || '');
    if (!datasetStr) {
      throw new Error('dataset empty for ' + auditNumber);
    }

    // --- Parse + normalize (scoring) ---
    var arr = JSON.parse(datasetStr);
    if (!Array.isArray(arr) || !arr.length) {
      throw new Error('dataset JSON empty');
    }

    function toNum(x){ 
      var n = Number(x); 
      return isFinite(n) ? n : 0; 
    }
    
    arr = arr.map(function(r){
      return {
        ai_score: toNum(r.ai_score),
        sex: (r.sex||'').trim(),
        race: (r.race||'').trim(),
        hispanic: (r.hispanic_or_latino==='1' || r.hispanic_or_latino===true)
      };
    });

    // --- Utils ---
    function mean(a){ 
      if (!a.length) return 0; 
      for (var s=0, i=0; i<a.length; i++) {
        s += a[i]; 
      }
      return s / a.length; 
    }
    
    function gb(list, key){ 
      var m={}; 
      for (var i=0; i<list.length; i++){ 
        var k = key(list[i]) || 'Unknown'; 
        (m[k] = m[k] || []).push(list[i]); 
      } 
      return m; 
    }
    
    function ir(map){
      var out = [], ks = Object.keys(map);
      var means = ks.map(function(k){ 
        return mean(map[k].map(function(x){return x.ai_score;})); 
      });
      var max = 0; 
      for (var i=0; i<means.length; i++) {
        if (means[i] > max) max = means[i];
      }
      for (var j=0; j<ks.length; j++){
        out.push({ 
          g: ks[j], 
          m: means[j], 
          ir: max ? means[j]/max : 0 
        });
      }
      out.sort(function(a,b){ return a.ir - b.ir; });
      return out;
    }
    
    function below(list){ 
      return list.filter(function(x){ return x.ir < THRESH; }); 
    }
    
    function roundAll(list){ 
      for (var i=0; i<list.length; i++){ 
        list[i].m = +list[i].m.toFixed(4); 
        list[i].ir = +list[i].ir.toFixed(6); 
      } 
    }

    // --- Groupings ---
    var bySex = gb(arr, function(x){return x.sex;});
    var byRace = gb(arr, function(x){return x.race;});
    var byHisp = gb(arr, function(x){return x.hispanic?'Hispanic':'Non-Hispanic';});
    var bySexRace = gb(arr, function(x){return (x.sex||'Unknown')+' | '+(x.race||'Unknown');});
    var byRaceHisp = gb(arr, function(x){return (x.race||'Unknown')+' | '+(x.hispanic?'Hispanic':'Non-Hispanic');});
    var bySexRaceHisp = gb(arr, function(x){return (x.sex||'Unknown')+' | '+(x.race||'Unknown')+' | '+(x.hispanic?'Hispanic':'Non-Hispanic');});

    // --- Compute IR and keep < 0.8 (compact) ---
    var bt = {
      r: below(ir(byRace)),
      sr: below(ir(bySexRace)),
      rh: below(ir(byRaceHisp)),
      srh: below(ir(bySexRaceHisp))
    };
    roundAll(bt.r); 
    roundAll(bt.sr); 
    roundAll(bt.rh); 
    roundAll(bt.srh);

    // --- Build minimal payload (n=audit number, m='S' for scoring) ---
    var payload = { n: auditNumber, m: 'S', t: THRESH, bt: bt };

    // --- Minify + enforce MAXLEN with pruning (worst IR kept first) ---
    var json = JSON.stringify(payload);
    if (json.length > MAXLEN) {
      function prune(list){ 
        if (!list || !list.length) return; 
        list.sort(function(a,b){return a.ir - b.ir;}); 
        list.pop(); 
      }
      var guard = 0;
      while (json.length > MAXLEN && guard < 10000) {
        if (bt.srh && bt.srh.length) prune(bt.srh);
        else if (bt.sr && bt.sr.length) prune(bt.sr);
        else if (bt.rh && bt.rh.length) prune(bt.rh);
        else if (bt.r && bt.r.length) prune(bt.r);
        else break;
        json = JSON.stringify(payload);
        guard++;
      }
    }

    // --- Write ---
    gr.setValue(F_OUT, json);
    var sysId = gr.update();

      // Send Data to n8n
     var payloadBody = JSON.stringify({
      results: payload,
      evidenceId: evidencePackId,
      biasSysId: inputs.bias_audit_sys_id
    });
    var request = new sn_ws.RESTMessageV2();
    request.setEndpoint(WEBHOOK_URL);
    request.setHttpMethod('POST');
    request.setRequestHeader('Content-Type', 'application/json');
    request.setRequestHeader('Accept', 'application/json');
    request.setRequestBody(payloadBody);
    var response = request.execute();

    // --- Return ---
    return {
      status: 'success',
      bias_audit_sys_id: biasAuditSysId,
      audit_number: auditNumber,
      stored_bytes: json.length,
      updated_sys_id: ''+sysId,
      payload_preview: json,
      res: response
    };

  } catch (e) {
    return { 
      status: 'error', 
      error: e.name + ': ' + e.message 
    };
  }
})(inputs);]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>frants.k</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-25 22:44:58</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>370ba2f983b432107f44e8be50da1e1d</sys_id><sys_mod_count>10</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Scoring Methodology</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_370ba2f983b432107f44e8be50da1e1d</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-27 22:24:02</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table>undefined</target_document_table><type>script</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sn_aia_tool_14abd7d783b432107f44e8be50da1ebd
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Creates detailed implementation guidance for high-risk policy changes</description><input_schema>[{"name":"alert_sys_id","description":""},{"name":"risk_level","description":""},{"name":"analysis_summary","description":""},{"name":"effective_date","description":""}]</input_schema><name>Generate Policy Guidance (High Risk - Manual)</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[(function(inputs) {
  try {
    gs.info('===== Tool 5: GENERATE POLICY GUIDANCE =====');
    
    // ===== INPUT VALIDATION =====
    var alertSysId = String(inputs.alert_sys_id || '').trim();
    var riskLevel = parseInt(inputs.risk_level || '0', 10);
    var impactAreasStr = String(inputs.impact_areas || '').trim();
    var affectedSystemsStr = String(inputs.affected_systems || '').trim();
    
    gs.info('Inputs:');
    gs.info('  alert_sys_id: ' + alertSysId);
    gs.info('  risk_level: ' + riskLevel);
    gs.info('  impact_areas: ' + impactAreasStr);
    gs.info('  affected_systems: ' + affectedSystemsStr);
    
    if (!alertSysId) {
      return {
        guidance_success: 'false',
        error: 'Missing required input: alert_sys_id'
      };
    }
    
    // ===== GET ALERT RECORD =====
    gs.info('Fetching alert record...');
    var alertGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_regulatory_alert_2');
    if (!alertGr.get(alertSysId)) {
      return {
        guidance_success: 'false',
        error: 'Alert not found: ' + alertSysId
      };
    }
    
    var alertNumber = alertGr.getValue('alert_number') || '';
    var title = alertGr.getValue('title') || '';
    var abstract = alertGr.getValue('abstract') || '';
    var regulationSource = alertGr.getValue('regulation_source') || '';
    var effectiveDate = alertGr.getValue('effective_date') || '';
    var documentNumber = alertGr.getValue('document_number') || '';
    var agencies = alertGr.getValue('agencies') || '';
    var sourceUrl = alertGr.getValue('source_url') || '';
    
    gs.info('Alert: ' + alertNumber + ' - ' + title.substring(0, 50));
    
    // Parse impact areas and affected systems
    var impactAreas = [];
    var affectedSystems = [];
    
    try {
      if (impactAreasStr.startsWith('[')) {
        impactAreas = JSON.parse(impactAreasStr);
      } else {
        impactAreas = impactAreasStr.split(',').map(function(s){ return s.trim(); }).filter(function(s){ return s; });
      }
    } catch (e) {
      gs.warn('Could not parse impact_areas: ' + e.message);
      impactAreas = [];
    }
    
    try {
      if (affectedSystemsStr.startsWith('[')) {
        affectedSystems = JSON.parse(affectedSystemsStr);
      } else {
        affectedSystems = affectedSystemsStr.split(',').map(function(s){ return s.trim(); }).filter(function(s){ return s; });
      }
    } catch (e) {
      gs.warn('Could not parse affected_systems: ' + e.message);
      affectedSystems = [];
    }
    
    gs.info('Impact areas: ' + impactAreas.join(', '));
    gs.info('Affected systems: ' + affectedSystems.join(', '));
    
    // ===== GENERATE COMPREHENSIVE POLICY GUIDANCE =====
    gs.info('Generating policy guidance document...');
    
    var guidanceText = '';
    
    // Header
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += '            HIGH-RISK REGULATORY COMPLIANCE GUIDANCE\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    // Alert Information
    guidanceText += 'ALERT INFORMATION:\n';
    guidanceText += '─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n';
    guidanceText += 'Alert Number: ' + alertNumber + '\n';
    guidanceText += 'Risk Level: ' + riskLevel + '/10 (HIGH RISK - MANUAL REVIEW REQUIRED)\n';
    guidanceText += 'Source: ' + regulationSource + '\n';
    guidanceText += 'Document: ' + documentNumber + '\n';
    guidanceText += 'Issuing Agency: ' + agencies + '\n';
    guidanceText += 'Effective Date: ' + effectiveDate + '\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'REGULATION TITLE:\n';
    guidanceText += title + '\n\n';
    
    // Executive Summary
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += '1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'This regulation has been classified as HIGH RISK (Level ' + riskLevel + '/10) ';
    guidanceText += 'and requires IMMEDIATE ATTENTION from senior leadership, legal counsel, ';
    guidanceText += 'and compliance teams.\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'CRITICAL: This regulatory change cannot be implemented through automated ';
    guidanceText += 'processes and requires manual policy review, legal analysis, and ';
    guidanceText += 'cross-functional coordination.\n\n';
    
    // Impact Analysis
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += '2. IMPACT ANALYSIS\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'Affected Business Areas:\n';
    if (impactAreas.length > 0) {
      for (var i = 0; i < impactAreas.length; i++) {
        guidanceText += '  • ' + impactAreas[i].replace(/_/g, ' ').toUpperCase() + '\n';
      }
    } else {
      guidanceText += '  • General compliance (requires detailed analysis)\n';
    }
    guidanceText += '\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'Affected AI Systems:\n';
    if (affectedSystems.length > 0) {
      for (var j = 0; j < affectedSystems.length; j++) {
        guidanceText += '  • ' + affectedSystems[j] + '\n';
      }
    } else {
      guidanceText += '  • All AI systems (requires review)\n';
    }
    guidanceText += '\n';
    
    // Why High Risk
    guidanceText += 'WHY THIS IS HIGH RISK:\n';
    guidanceText += 'This regulation likely involves one or more of the following:\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Fundamental methodology changes requiring new processes\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Immediate compliance deadlines with limited preparation time\n';
    guidanceText += '  • System suspension or operational changes affecting business continuity\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Significant penalty exposure for non-compliance\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Complex implementation requiring cross-functional coordination\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Legal interpretation needed before action can be taken\n\n';
    
    // Recommended Actions
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += '3. RECOMMENDED ACTIONS (PRIORITY ORDER)\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    // FIXED: All GlideDateTime operations
    var urgentDeadline = new GlideDateTime();
    urgentDeadline.addDaysUTC(3);
    
    var legalReviewDeadline = new GlideDateTime();
    legalReviewDeadline.addDaysUTC(5);
    
    var implementationDeadline = new GlideDateTime();
    implementationDeadline.addDaysUTC(7);
    
    var complianceReviewDeadline = new GlideDateTime();
    complianceReviewDeadline.addDaysUTC(10);
    
    guidanceText += 'IMMEDIATE (Within 24-48 Hours):\n';
    guidanceText += '1. Convene emergency compliance meeting with:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Chief Compliance Officer\n';
    guidanceText += '   • General Counsel / Legal Team\n';
    guidanceText += '   • HR Leadership (if employment AI affected)\n';
    guidanceText += '   • IT/Engineering Leadership\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Risk Management\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '2. Conduct initial impact assessment:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Review full regulation text and legal analysis\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Identify all affected AI systems and processes\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Assess current compliance gaps\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Estimate resource requirements\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'URGENT (By ' + urgentDeadline.getDisplayValue() + '):\n';
    guidanceText += '3. Legal review and interpretation:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Engage external legal counsel if needed\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Document legal obligations and requirements\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Identify compliance risks and mitigation strategies\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Determine if business process changes are required\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '4. Risk assessment:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Calculate potential penalty exposure\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Assess business continuity impact\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Identify resource constraints\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Evaluate timeline feasibility\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'SHORT-TERM (By ' + legalReviewDeadline.getDisplayValue() + '):\n';
    guidanceText += '5. Develop compliance implementation plan:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Define specific compliance requirements\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Assign ownership and accountability\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Create detailed project timeline\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Allocate budget and resources\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Establish success criteria and KPIs\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '6. Stakeholder communication:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Brief executive leadership on requirements and risks\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Notify affected business units\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Prepare employee communications if needed\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Coordinate with external auditors if applicable\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'MEDIUM-TERM (By ' + implementationDeadline.getDisplayValue() + '):\n';
    guidanceText += '7. Begin implementation:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Update policies and procedures\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Modify AI systems and processes as required\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Conduct employee training\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Update documentation and audit trails\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Implement monitoring and reporting mechanisms\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '8. Testing and validation:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Test updated systems and processes\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Validate compliance with new requirements\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Document test results and evidence\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Address any gaps or issues identified\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'ONGOING (By ' + complianceReviewDeadline.getDisplayValue() + '):\n';
    guidanceText += '9. Compliance monitoring:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Establish regular compliance checks\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Monitor for additional regulatory updates\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Maintain audit-ready documentation\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Review and refine processes as needed\n\n';
    
    // Specific Guidance by Impact Area
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += '4. SPECIFIC GUIDANCE BY IMPACT AREA\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    // Methodology changes
    if (impactAreas.indexOf('statistical_methodology') > -1 || impactAreas.indexOf('bias_audits') > -1) {
      guidanceText += 'BIAS AUDIT METHODOLOGY:\n';
      guidanceText += '• Engage independent bias audit vendor immediately\n';
      guidanceText += '• Review and update statistical methodologies\n';
      guidanceText += '• Re-run audits using updated methodology\n';
      guidanceText += '• Document methodology changes thoroughly\n';
      guidanceText += '• Ensure auditor credentials meet new requirements\n\n';
    }
    
    // AI system changes
    if (impactAreas.indexOf('ai_systems') > -1) {
      guidanceText += 'AI SYSTEM MODIFICATIONS:\n';
      guidanceText += '• Conduct technical feasibility assessment\n';
      guidanceText += '• Determine if systems need suspension during updates\n';
      guidanceText += '• Plan for business continuity during changes\n';
      guidanceText += '• Update system documentation and configurations\n';
      guidanceText += '• Re-validate AI system performance after changes\n\n';
    }
    
    // Evidence and documentation
    if (impactAreas.indexOf('evidence_packs') > -1 || impactAreas.indexOf('documentation') > -1) {
      guidanceText += 'EVIDENCE & DOCUMENTATION:\n';
      guidanceText += '• Review all existing evidence packs for completeness\n';
      guidanceText += '• Update evidence pack templates and requirements\n';
      guidanceText += '• Ensure evidence retention meets new standards\n';
      guidanceText += '• Implement version control for compliance documents\n';
      guidanceText += '• Create audit trail of all compliance activities\n\n';
    }
    
    // Transparency and reporting
    if (impactAreas.indexOf('transparency') > -1 || impactAreas.indexOf('compliance_reporting') > -1) {
      guidanceText += 'TRANSPARENCY & REPORTING:\n';
      guidanceText += '• Develop candidate/applicant disclosure materials\n';
      guidanceText += '• Update privacy notices and consent forms\n';
      guidanceText += '• Create process for human review requests\n';
      guidanceText += '• Establish transparency reporting schedule\n';
      guidanceText += '• Prepare for regulatory reporting requirements\n\n';
    }
    
    // Registration and certification
    if (impactAreas.indexOf('compliance_reporting') > -1) {
      guidanceText += 'REGISTRATION & CERTIFICATION:\n';
      guidanceText += '• Identify registration requirements and deadlines\n';
      guidanceText += '• Gather required system documentation\n';
      guidanceText += '• Complete registration applications\n';
      guidanceText += '• Budget for registration and certification fees\n';
      guidanceText += '• Schedule third-party audits if required\n\n';
    }
    
    // Resources and Budget
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += '5. RESOURCES & BUDGET CONSIDERATIONS\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'Estimated Resource Requirements:\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Legal Counsel: 40-60 hours (internal + external)\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Compliance Team: 80-120 hours\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Engineering/IT: 60-100 hours\n';
    guidanceText += '  • HR/Business Units: 40-60 hours\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Executive Leadership: 10-20 hours\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'Estimated Budget Impact:\n';
    guidanceText += '  • External Legal Review: $15,000 - $30,000\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Third-Party Audit Services: $10,000 - $25,000\n';
    guidanceText += '  • System Modifications: $20,000 - $50,000\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Training & Documentation: $5,000 - $10,000\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Registration/Certification Fees: $5,000 - $15,000\n';
    guidanceText += '  • TOTAL ESTIMATED COST: $55,000 - $130,000\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'Note: Costs vary based on organization size, complexity, and\n';
    guidanceText += 'existing compliance infrastructure. Budget for contingencies.\n\n';
    
    // Risk Mitigation
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += '6. RISK MITIGATION STRATEGIES\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'COMPLIANCE RISKS:\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Penalty Exposure: $500 - $50,000 per violation (varies by regulation)\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Reputational Damage: Public disclosure of non-compliance\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Litigation Risk: Discrimination lawsuits from affected candidates\n';
    guidanceText += '  • Operational Impact: System suspension or usage restrictions\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'MITIGATION ACTIONS:\n';
    guidanceText += '1. Engage proactively with regulatory agencies\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Request guidance on interpretation\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Seek safe harbor or transition period if available\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Document good faith compliance efforts\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '2. Consider temporary measures:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Voluntary system suspension until compliant\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Enhanced human oversight during transition\n';
    guidanceText += '   • More frequent bias audits during implementation\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '3. Insurance and liability review:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Review E&O and cyber liability coverage\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Consider additional coverage if gaps exist\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Document risk mitigation efforts for insurers\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '4. Contingency planning:\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Develop rollback plan if implementation fails\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Create manual process alternatives\n';
    guidanceText += '   • Establish crisis communication protocols\n\n';
    
    // Documentation Requirements
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += '7. DOCUMENTATION REQUIREMENTS\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'Maintain comprehensive documentation of:\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ All compliance meetings and decisions\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ Legal analysis and opinions received\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ Risk assessments and mitigation strategies\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ Implementation plans and timelines\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ System modifications and testing results\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ Training materials and attendance records\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ Audit results and corrective actions\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ All communications with regulatory agencies\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ Budget approvals and expenditures\n';
    guidanceText += '  ✓ Ongoing monitoring and compliance checks\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'Documentation Retention: Minimum 7 years from effective date\n\n';
    
    // Next Steps
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += '8. IMMEDIATE NEXT STEPS\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    // FIXED: Use addDaysUTC(2) instead of addHoursUTC(48)
    var nextStepDeadline = new GlideDateTime();
    nextStepDeadline.addDaysUTC(2); // 2 days (48 hours)
    
    guidanceText += 'ACTION REQUIRED BY ' + nextStepDeadline.getDisplayValue() + ':\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '1. SCHEDULE EMERGENCY MEETING\n';
    guidanceText += '   Attendees: CCO, General Counsel, HR Lead, IT Lead, Risk Manager\n';
    guidanceText += '   Agenda: Review this guidance, assess impact, assign ownership\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '2. READ FULL REGULATION\n';
    guidanceText += '   Access regulation text at: ' + (sourceUrl || '[URL in alert record]') + '\n';
    guidanceText += '   Prepare summary of key requirements\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '3. ASSESS CURRENT STATE\n';
    guidanceText += '   Document: What we do now vs. what regulation requires\n';
    guidanceText += '   Identify: Specific gaps and needed changes\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '4. ENGAGE LEGAL COUNSEL\n';
    guidanceText += '   Internal counsel review + consider external expertise\n';
    guidanceText += '   Request written legal opinion on requirements\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += '5. NOTIFY EXECUTIVES\n';
    guidanceText += '   Brief: CEO, CFO, Board if material impact\n';
    guidanceText += '   Request: Budget approval for implementation\n\n';
    
    // Footer
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n';
    guidanceText += 'END OF POLICY GUIDANCE DOCUMENT\n';
    guidanceText += '═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n';
    
    var docGeneratedTime = new GlideDateTime();
    guidanceText += 'Document Generated: ' + docGeneratedTime.getDisplayValue() + '\n';
    guidanceText += 'Alert Reference: ' + alertNumber + '\n';
    guidanceText += 'Risk Classification: HIGH (Level ' + riskLevel + '/10)\n';
    guidanceText += 'Status: MANUAL REVIEW REQUIRED - DO NOT AUTO-EXECUTE\n\n';
    
    guidanceText += 'CRITICAL REMINDER:\n';
    guidanceText += 'This guidance document is for informational purposes only and does\n';
    guidanceText += 'not constitute legal advice. Consult with qualified legal counsel\n';
    guidanceText += 'before taking action on any regulatory compliance matter.\n';
    
    gs.info('Policy guidance document generated (' + guidanceText.length + ' characters)');
    
    // ===== CREATE GUIDANCE RECORD =====
    gs.info('Creating policy guidance record...');
    
    var guidanceGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_x_snc_ai_complia_1_regulatory_alert');
    guidanceGr.initialize();
    guidanceGr.setValue('regulatory_alert', alertSysId);
    guidanceGr.setValue('risk_level', riskLevel);
    guidanceGr.setValue('guidance_text', guidanceText);
    guidanceGr.setValue('status', 'pending_review');
    guidanceGr.setValue('assigned_to', ''); // Leave empty for manual assignment
    
    var createdDate = new GlideDateTime();
    guidanceGr.setValue('created_date', createdDate.getValue());
    
    var guidanceSysId = guidanceGr.insert();
    
    if (!guidanceSysId) {
      gs.error('Failed to create policy guidance record');
      return {
        guidance_success: 'false',
        error: 'Failed to create policy guidance record'
      };
    }
    
    gs.info('✓ Policy guidance record created: ' + guidanceSysId);
    
    // ===== UPDATE ALERT STATUS =====
    gs.info('Updating alert status...');
    
    alertGr.setValue('status', 'manual_review_required');
    
    var reviewDate = new GlideDateTime();
    alertGr.setValue('manual_review_date', reviewDate.getValue());
    
    alertGr.update();
    
    gs.info('✓ Alert status updated to manual_review_required');
    
    gs.info('===== Tool 5: COMPLETE =====');
    
    // ===== RETURN RESULTS =====
    return {
      guidance_success: 'true',
      alert_sys_id: alertSysId,
      alert_number: alertNumber,
      guidance_sys_id: guidanceSysId,
      guidance_length: String(guidanceText.length),
      status: 'Policy guidance generated - manual review required'
    };
    
  } catch (e) {
    gs.error('===== Tool 5 ERROR =====');
    gs.error('Error: ' + e.message);
    gs.error('Stack: ' + e.stack);
    
    return {
      guidance_success: 'false',
      error: e.message
    };
  }
})(inputs);]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sophia.rafat</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-30 18:08:03</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>14abd7d783b432107f44e8be50da1ebd</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Generate Policy Guidance (High Risk - Manual)</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_14abd7d783b432107f44e8be50da1ebd</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sophia.rafat</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-30 18:22:54</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table/><type>script</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Updates all processed alerts to "Under Review"</description><input_schema>[{"name":"recommendations_final","description":""}]</input_schema><name>Update Alert Status (Loop)</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[
(function(inputs) {
    
    gs.info('===== TOOL 5: Update Alert Status =====');
    
    var recommendationsJson = inputs.recommendations_final || '[]';
    
    var recommendations = [];
    try {
        recommendations = JSON.parse(recommendationsJson);
    } catch (parseError) {
        gs.error('Failed to parse recommendations: ' + parseError.message);
        return {
            alerts_updated: 'false',
            update_count: '0'
        };
    }
    
    if (recommendations.length === 0) {
        return {
            alerts_updated: 'false',
            update_count: '0'
        };
    }
    
    // Get AI Compliance Team group
    var group = new GlideRecord('sys_user_group');
    group.addQuery('name', 'AI Compliance Team');
    group.query();
    var groupId = group.next() ? group.sys_id.toString() : '';
    
    var updatedCount = 0;
    
    for (var i = 0; i < recommendations.length; i++) {
        var rec = recommendations[i];
        
        try {
            var alertGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_regulatory_alert_2');
            if (alertGr.get(rec.alert_sys_id)) {
                alertGr.status = 'Under Review';
                alertGr.assigned_group = groupId;
                alertGr.analysis_date = new GlideDateTime();
                alertGr.update();
                updatedCount++;
            }
        } catch (ex) {
            gs.error('Failed to update alert: ' + ex.message);
        }
    }
    
    gs.info('════════════════════════════════════════');
    gs.info('✅ Batch Processing Complete');
    gs.info('════════════════════════════════════════');
    gs.info('Alerts Processed: ' + recommendations.length);
    gs.info('Recommendations Created: ' + recommendations.length);
    gs.info('Tasks Created: ' + recommendations.length);
    gs.info('Alerts Updated: ' + updatedCount);
    gs.info('════════════════════════════════════════');
    
    return {
        alerts_updated: 'true',
        update_count: String(updatedCount)
    };
    
})(inputs);]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sophia.rafat</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-31 22:11:03</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>e1dc597b83b472107f44e8be50da1e7e</sys_id><sys_mod_count>2</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Update Alert Status (Loop)</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_e1dc597b83b472107f44e8be50da1e7e</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sophia.rafat</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-31 23:14:58</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table/><type>script</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Automatically executes low-risk compliance updates without user approval</description><input_schema>[{"name":"alert_sys_id","description":""},{"name":"action_type","description":""},{"name":"affected_system","description":""},{"name":"impact_areas","description":""}]</input_schema><name>Execute Data Updates (Low Risk - Auto)</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[(function(inputs) {
  var alertSysId = String(inputs.alert_sys_id || '').trim();
  var actionType = String(inputs.action_type || '').trim();
  var affectedSystemsJson = String(inputs.affected_systems || '[]');
  var impactAreasJson = String(inputs.impact_areas || '[]');
  
  gs.info('===== Tool 2: EXECUTE DATA UPDATES =====');
  gs.info('Alert sys_id: ' + alertSysId);
  
  try {
    var affectedSystems = JSON.parse(affectedSystemsJson);
    var impactAreas = JSON.parse(impactAreasJson);
  } catch (e) {
    return {
      actions_executed: '0',
      success: 'false',
      error: 'Invalid JSON input'
    };
  }
  
  var actionsExecuted = 0;
  var actionSysIds = [];
  
  // ACTION 1: Update AI System Metadata
  if (impactAreas.indexOf('ai_systems') > -1) {
    gs.info('Updating AI system metadata...');
    
    for (var i = 0; i < affectedSystems.length; i++) {
      var systemName = affectedSystems[i];
      
      var aiGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_ai_systems');
      aiGr.addQuery('name', systemName);
      aiGr.query();
      
      if (aiGr.next()) {
        // Add compliance tag
        var currentTags = aiGr.getValue('compliance_tags') || '';
        if (currentTags.indexOf('regulatory_update_pending') === -1) {
          aiGr.setValue('compliance_tags', currentTags + ',regulatory_update_pending');
        }
        
        // Update next audit date if needed
        var nextAudit = new GlideDateTime();
        nextAudit.addDaysUTC(30); // Schedule audit in 30 days
        aiGr.setValue('next_audit_date', nextAudit.getValue());
        
        aiGr.update();
        actionsExecuted++;
        
        // Create action record
        var actionGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_recommended_actions_2');
        actionGr.initialize();
        actionGr.setValue('regulatory_alert', alertSysId);
        actionGr.setValue('action_type', 'auto_execute');
        actionGr.setValue('action_category', 'data_update');
        actionGr.setValue('action_description', 'Updated metadata for ' + systemName);
        actionGr.setValue('risk_level', 'low');
        actionGr.setValue('status', 'executed');
        actionGr.setValue('requires_approval', false);
        actionGr.setValue('executed_date', new GlideDateTime().getValue());
        actionGr.setValue('execution_result', 'success');
        var actionId = actionGr.insert();
        actionSysIds.push(actionId);
        
        gs.info('Updated AI system: ' + systemName);
      }
    }
  }
  
  // Send notification
  var notificationSent = false;
  try {
    gs.eventQueue('ai_compliance.regulatory_alert.auto_actions', 
                   null, 
                   alertSysId, 
                   actionsExecuted + ' automatic actions executed');
    notificationSent = true;
  } catch (e) {
    gs.error('Failed to send notification: ' + e.message);
  }
  
  // Update alert status
  var alertGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_regulatory_alert');
  if (alertGr.get(alertSysId)) {
    alertGr.setValue('status', 'completed');
    alertGr.update();
  }
  
  gs.info('Tool 2: Complete - ' + actionsExecuted + ' actions executed');
  
  return {
    actions_executed: String(actionsExecuted),
    success: 'true',
    action_sys_ids: JSON.stringify(actionSysIds),
    notification_sent: String(notificationSent)
  };
})(inputs);]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sophia.rafat</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-30 18:08:04</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>9cabd7d783b432107f44e8be50da1ec2</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Execute Data Updates (Low Risk - Auto)</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_9cabd7d783b432107f44e8be50da1ec2</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sophia.rafat</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-30 18:24:32</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table/><type>script</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ws_operation"><sys_ws_operation action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><consumes>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</consumes><consumes_customized>false</consumes_customized><default_operation_uri/><enforce_acl>cf9d01d3e73003009d6247e603f6a990</enforce_acl><http_method>POST</http_method><name>Update Feedback</name><operation_script><![CDATA[(function process(/*RESTAPIRequest*/ request, /*RESTAPIResponse*/ response) {
    try {
        var body = request.body.data;

        if (!body || !body.enrollmentID) {
            response.setStatus(400);
            return { error: "Missing required field: enrollmentID" };
        }

        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_training_enrollments');
        gr.addQuery('number', body.enrollmentID);
        gr.query();

		
        if (gr.next()) {
			
			// Training Enrollments 
            gr.setValue('feedback', body.feedback);
            gr.update();
			
            response.setStatus(200);
            return {
                message: "Feedback provided successfully",
                enrollmentID: body.enrollmentID
            };
        } else {
            response.setStatus(404);
            return { error: "Enrollment not found" };
        }
    } catch (e) {
        gs.error("Scripted REST API error: " + e.message);
        response.setStatus(500);
        return { error: "Internal server error" };
    }
})(request, response);
]]></operation_script><operation_uri>/api/x_snc_ai_complia_0/ai_literacy/updatefeedback</operation_uri><produces>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</produces><produces_customized>false</produces_customized><relative_path>/updatefeedback</relative_path><request_example/><requires_acl_authorization>true</requires_acl_authorization><requires_authentication>true</requires_authentication><requires_snc_internal_role>true</requires_snc_internal_role><short_description/><sys_class_name>sys_ws_operation</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-21 02:25:42</sys_created_on><sys_id>01cc295c83b072107f44e8be50da1e98</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Update Feedback</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ws_operation_01cc295c83b072107f44e8be50da1e98</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-21 02:25:42</sys_updated_on><web_service_definition display_value="AI Literacy">fb8d0a37836032107f44e8be50da1ed9</web_service_definition><web_service_version/></sys_ws_operation></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_agent"><sn_aia_agent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><description>This agent automates NYC Local Law 144 bias auditing by: 1. Retrieving applicants filtered by AI system 2. Validating and transforming data based on audit type (Internal Selection or Internal Scoring) 3. Creating batch audit records with required demographic data 4. Performing quality verification on created records 5. Logging comprehensive audit trails
The agent ensures data integrity through validation, sampling verification, and maintains compliance with NYC reporting requirements.</description><instructions>You are a specialized compliance automation agent for NYC Local Law 144 bias auditing.
ALLOWED AI SYSTEMS (user MUST choose one of these):
Resume Scanner
Video Interview Analysis Software (VIAS)
Predictive Hiring Tools
ALLOWED AUDIT TYPES (user MUST choose one of these):
Internal Selection
Internal Scoring
ALWAYS follow these steps in exact order
STEP 1: RECEIVE AND VALIDATE USER INPUT
ALWAYS collect ai_system_name from the user.
ALWAYS collect audit_type from the user.
ALWAYS validate ai_system_name is EXACTLY one of: Resume Scanner, Video Interview Analysis Software (VIAS), Predictive Hiring Tools.
ALWAYS validate audit_type is EXACTLY "Internal Selection" OR "Internal Scoring" (case-sensitive, with exact spelling).
If ai_system_name is NOT in allowed list, STOP and say: "Please select one of these AI systems: Resume Scanner, Video Interview Analysis Software (VIAS), or Predictive Hiring Tools."
If audit_type is NOT valid, STOP and say: "Please select either 'Internal Selection' or 'Internal Scoring' (exact spelling and capitalization required)."
DO NOT proceed without valid inputs.
DO NOT call any tools until inputs are validated.
Proceed to STEP 2.
STEP 2: QUERY APPLICANTS
ALWAYS use Tool 1 (Query Applicants).
ALWAYS pass: - ai_system_name: Pass the ai_system_name from user input in STEP 1 - audit_type: Pass the audit_type from user input in STEP 1
Tool 1 will query the applicants table where ai_system (string field) matches the name exactly, and return ALL applicant records including both status and ai_score fields.
IMPORTANT: Applicant data is ANONYMIZED - no sys_id or personally identifiable information is included in the output.
WAIT for Tool 1 to complete and read: - applicant_records_ndjson_blob (NDJSON string; one JSON object per line; no [ or ]) - total_records - query_status
If query_status = "error", STOP and report error.
If total_records = 0, STOP and say: "No applicant records found for the AI system. Please verify the system name matches exactly what is stored in the database."
If total_records > 500, inform the user: "Large dataset detected - {total_records} records. Processing may take longer than usual."
DO NOT attempt to parse or manipulate the applicant_records_ndjson_blob string. Pass it directly to Tool 2 as-is.
Proceed to STEP 3.
STEP 3: VALIDATE AND BUILD DATASET
ALWAYS use Tool 2 (Validate and Build Dataset).
ALWAYS pass: - applicant_records_ndjson_blob from Tool 1 - audit_type from STEP 1 - ai_system_name from STEP 1
Tool 2 MUST: - Parse the NDJSON input (one JSON object per line) - Validate required fields based on audit_type: * Internal Selection → require sex, race, status (plus hispanic_or_latino if present) * Internal Scoring → require sex, race, ai_score (plus hispanic_or_latino if present) - Build a single validated ANONYMIZED dataset covering all valid applicants - Order fields appropriately: * Internal Selection: status, sex, race, hispanic_or_latino * Internal Scoring: ai_score, sex, race, hispanic_or_latino - Return dataset_ndjson_blob (NDJSON string; one JSON object per line; no [ or ])
Tool 2 returns: - dataset_ndjson_blob (validated NDJSON) - records_valid - records_invalid - failure_rate - validation_metrics_json - canProceed - audit_type_out (pass-through) - ai_system_name (pass-through) - audit_date_out (generated)
If canProceed = "false" OR failure_rate > 5%, STOP and report validation issues to the user with details from validation_metrics_json.
If OK, proceed to STEP 4.
STEP 4: CREATE BIAS AUDIT RECORD
ALWAYS use Tool 3 (Create Bias Audit Record).
ALWAYS pass these parameters from Tool 2 outputs: - dataset_ndjson_blob (from Tool 2) - audit_type_out (from Tool 2) - ai_system_name (from Tool 2) - audit_date_out (from Tool 2)
Tool 3 MUST: - Look up the AI System by name to get its sys_id (if ai_system is a reference field) - Convert the NDJSON string to a JSON array string server-side (adds brackets and commas) - Store the JSON array in the Bias Audit record's dataset field - Set fields: * ai_system (reference to AI System record by sys_id, or string value if lookup fails) * audit_type * audit_date (date-only format) * dataset (JSON array string - anonymized data) * result = "pending" * validation_status = "valid" * created_by_agent = "Data Prep Agent" - Insert exactly ONE record in x_snc_ai_complia_0_bias_audits table - Return the bias_audit_sys_id for downstream processing
Tool 3 returns: - records_created (expect "1") - records_failed - creation_summary_json - created_record_ids_json - bias_audit_sys_id (sys_id of created Bias Audit record)
If records_created = "0", STOP and report the insert error with details from creation_summary_json.
If records_created = "1", proceed IMMEDIATELY to STEP 5.
STEP 5: CREATE EVIDENCE PACK AND UPDATE BIAS AUDIT
After Tool 3 completes successfully, IMMEDIATELY use Tool 4 (Create Evidence Pack and Update Bias Audit).
DO NOT ask the user for help. DO NOT wait for confirmation. AUTOMATICALLY execute Tool 4.
ALWAYS pass: - bias_audit_sys_id: Use the bias_audit_sys_id from Tool 3 output
Tool 4 will AUTOMATICALLY: - Create a new Evidence Pack record - Retrieve the auto-generated Evidence Pack number field - Update the Bias Audit record's evidence field with the Evidence Pack number
Tool 4 returns: - success (expect "true") - evidence_pack_sys_id - evidence_number
If success = "false", STOP and report the error from Tool 4.
If success = "true", proceed to STEP 6.
STEP 6: REPORT RESULTS TO USER
ALWAYS provide a concise summary: - AI System name (from user input) - Audit Type (from user input) - Total records queried (from Tool 1: total_records) - Records validated successfully (from Tool 2: records_valid) - Records failed validation (from Tool 2: records_invalid) - Bias Audit record created (expect 1) - Bias Audit Record ID (from Tool 3: bias_audit_sys_id) - Evidence Pack Number (from Tool 4: evidence_number)
STEP 7: PASS TO BIASED CATEGORIES SELECTOR
After successfully creating the Bias Audit record:
1. Take the bias_audit_sys_id from Tool 3 output 2. Pass it to the "Biased Categories Selector" agent as audit_number
If bias_audit_sys_id is empty, STOP and report: "Failed to create Bias Audit record. Cannot proceed to category selection."
Otherwise, inform the user: "Bias Audit record created. Proceeding to category selection..."
Format example: "✓ Bias Audit Created Successfully
AI System: Resume Scanner Audit Type: Internal Selection Total Applicants: 100 Valid Records: 98 Invalid Records: 2 Bias Audit Record ID: abc123xyz456 Evidence Pack: EP0001234
Note: All applicant data has been anonymized per NYC Local Law 144 requirements."
DO NOT include raw JSON blobs in the user-facing summary.
ALWAYS format the output in a clean, user-friendly manner.
ERROR HANDLING
If any tool fails at any step, STOP immediately and report the specific error to the user.
If validation failure rate exceeds 5% in STEP 3, STOP and report which records failed and why.
DO NOT retry failed tools without explicit user confirmation.
If no applicants are found in STEP 2, STOP with a clear message.
If Tool 4 fails (success = "false"), STOP and report the error message.
ERROR RECOVERY
If you encounter "SyntaxError: Unexpected token: ]" error: 1. Check that Tool 1 output does NOT contain brackets [ or ] 2. Verify the NDJSON string is being passed directly to Tool 2 without modification 3. Do NOT try to parse the NDJSON yourself - let Tool 2 handle it 4. If error persists, inform the user: "There's an issue with the data format. Please contact your administrator to check the Tool 1 output format."
If the agent framework throws a parsing error: 1. Log the error details 2. Inform the user which step failed 3. Do NOT retry automatically 4. Ask user if they want to retry with the same inputs
CRITICAL NOTES
- Tool 1 fetches ALL applicant fields (status AND ai_score) regardless of audit_type - Tool 2 validates which fields are required based on audit_type - DATA IS ANONYMIZED: No applicant sys_id or personally identifiable information is included - Field order matters: * Internal Selection records start with "status" field * Internal Scoring records start with "ai_score" field - NDJSON format = one JSON object per line, NO brackets [ ], NO trailing commas - Tool 3 converts NDJSON to JSON array (adds brackets) before storing in database - audit_type values are case-sensitive: "Internal Selection" and "Internal Scoring" - ai_system_name must match EXACTLY what is stored in the applicants table ai_system field - NEVER attempt to parse or manipulate NDJSON strings - always pass them as raw strings between tools - Tool 4 is AUTOMATICALLY executed after Tool 3 - do not ask the user for permission - Tool 4 handles both Evidence Pack creation and Bias Audit update in a single operation - All data complies with NYC Local Law 144 privacy and anonymization requirements
PARAMETER MAPPING REFERENCE
Tool 1 Inputs: - ai_system_name (from user input - STEP 1) - audit_type (from user input - STEP 1)
Tool 1 Outputs: - applicant_records_ndjson_blob (pass to Tool 2) - ANONYMIZED - total_records - query_status
Tool 2 Inputs: - applicant_records_ndjson_blob (from Tool 1 output) - audit_type (from user input - STEP 1) - ai_system_name (from user input - STEP 1)
Tool 2 Outputs: - dataset_ndjson_blob (pass to Tool 3) - ANONYMIZED with proper field order - audit_type_out (pass to Tool 3) - ai_system_name (pass to Tool 3) - audit_date_out (pass to Tool 3) - records_valid - records_invalid - failure_rate - canProceed - validation_metrics_json
Tool 3 Inputs: - dataset_ndjson_blob (from Tool 2 output) - audit_type_out (from Tool 2 output) - ai_system_name (from Tool 2 output) - audit_date_out (from Tool 2 output)
Tool 3 Outputs: - records_created - records_failed - creation_summary_json - created_record_ids_json - bias_audit_sys_id (pass to Tool 4) (pass to Biased Categories Selector Agent)
Tool 4 Inputs: - bias_audit_sys_id (from Tool 3 output)
Tool 4 Outputs: - success - evidence_pack_sys_id - evidence_number
DATA FORMAT EXAMPLES
Internal Selection NDJSON format (status first): {"status":"moved_forward","sex":"female","race":"asian","hispanic_or_latino":false} {"status":"rejected","sex":"male","race":"white","hispanic_or_latino":true}
Internal Scoring NDJSON format (ai_score first): {"ai_score":85,"sex":"female","race":"asian","hispanic_or_latino":false} {"ai_score":72,"sex":"male","race":"white","hispanic_or_latino":true}
IMPORTANT: Never try to parse NDJSON strings yourself. Always pass them as raw strings between tools. The NDJSON format is only converted to a JSON array inside Tool 3's server-side code.</instructions><internal_name>global.x_snc_ai_complia_0.Data Prep Agent</internal_name><name>Data Prep Agent</name><proficiency>- The agent is proficient in preparing and managing applicant data specifically for bias audits, ensuring that all data is collected, filtered, and formatted according to compliance standards. This involves understanding the nuances of bias auditing and the specific requirements of NYC Local Law 144. - The agent can query and retrieve anonymized applicant data from the database using the 'Query Applicants' tool. This involves validating user inputs for AI system name and audit type, and handling errors if the inputs are invalid or if no records are found. - The agent is capable of validating and transforming applicant data into an audit-ready format using the 'Validate and Build Dataset' tool. This includes checking for required fields, ordering data correctly, and ensuring the failure rate is within acceptable limits. - The agent can create a bias audit record in the system using the 'Create Bias Audit Record' tool. This involves converting NDJSON to a JSON array, storing it in the database, and setting various fields to ensure the audit record is complete and valid. - The agent can automatically create an evidence pack and update the bias audit record using the 'Create Evidence Pack and Update Bias Audit' tool. This ensures that the audit process is fully documented and compliant with legal requirements.</proficiency><record_type>custom</record_type><role>You are a data preparation agent. Your purpose is to collect, filter, and format applicant data for bias audits, and to create a Bias Audit record in the system.</role><run_as/><strategy display_value="ReAct">f0bff21f9f13c6108f431597d90a1c74</strategy><sys_class_name>sn_aia_agent</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>frants.k</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-25 22:37:45</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>625922f583b432107f44e8be50da1e36</sys_id><sys_mod_count>7</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Data Prep Agent</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_agent_625922f583b432107f44e8be50da1e36</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>frants.k</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-27 01:11:44</sys_updated_on></sn_aia_agent></record_update>
