sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Select categories with IR <0.8 using selection methodology</description><input_schema>[{"name":"dataset_str","description":""},{"name":"bias_audit_sys_id","description":""}]</input_schema><name>Selection Methodology</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[(function selection_and_store_compact(inputs) {
  try {
    // --- config ---
    var TABLE = 'x_snc_ai_complia_0_bias_audits';
    var F_NUM = 'number';
    var F_DATA = 'dataset';
    var F_OUT = 'u_0_8_selection_impact_ratio';
    var THRESH = 0.8;
    var MAXLEN = 10000;
    var WEBHOOK_URL = 'https://gracesolutionsdev.app.n8n.cloud/webhook/6cf0c534-644a-4baf-80e7-5ceb9e827608';
    // --- Get bias_audit_sys_id (sys_id only) ---
    var biasAuditSysId = (inputs && inputs.bias_audit_sys_id) ? (''+inputs.bias_audit_sys_id).trim() : '';
    if (!biasAuditSysId) {
      throw new Error('bias_audit_sys_id is required');
    }

    // --- Fetch record by sys_id ---
    var gr = new GlideRecord(TABLE);
    if (!gr.get(biasAuditSysId)) {
      throw new Error('Bias Audit not found: ' + biasAuditSysId);
    }
    var evidencePackId = gr.getValue('evidence');
    // --- Get audit number for payload ---
    var auditNumber = (''+gr.getValue(F_NUM)).trim();
    if (!auditNumber) {
      throw new Error('Record has no audit number');
    }

    // --- Get dataset ---
    var datasetStr = '' + (gr.getValue(F_DATA) || '');
    if (!datasetStr) {
      throw new Error('dataset empty for ' + auditNumber);
    }

    // --- Parse + normalize (Selection) ---
    var arr = JSON.parse(datasetStr);
    if (!Array.isArray(arr) || !arr.length) {
      throw new Error('dataset JSON empty');
    }

    function toBoolSelected(v){
      if (v === true) return true;
      if (v === false) return false;
      var s = (''+v).toLowerCase().replace(/[_\-]/g,' ').replace(/\s+/g,' ').trim();
      if (!s) return false;
      var neg = ['reject','rejected','decline','declined','fail','failed','no hire','nohire','not selected','did not advance','didn\'t advance'];
      for (var i=0; i<neg.length; i++) {
        if (s.indexOf(neg[i]) >= 0) return false;
      }
      var posRe = /(moved\s*forward|move\s*forward|advance(d)?|progress(ed)?|promote(d)?|select(ed)?|hire(d)?|offer(ed)?|accept(ed)?|pass(ed)?)/;
      if (posRe.test(s)) return true;
      if (s === '1' || s === 'true' || s === 'yes') return true;
      if (s === '0' || s === 'false' || s === 'no') return false;
      return false;
    }

    arr = arr.map(function(r){
      return {
        sel: toBoolSelected(r.status || r.decision || r.selected || r.hired),
        sex: (r.sex||'').trim(),
        race: (r.race||'').trim(),
        hispanic: (r.hispanic_or_latino==='1'||r.hispanic_or_latino===true)
      };
    });

    // --- Utils ---
    function gb(list, key){ 
      var m={}; 
      for (var i=0; i<list.length; i++){ 
        var k=key(list[i])||'Unknown'; 
        (m[k]=m[k]||[]).push(list[i]); 
      } 
      return m; 
    }
    
    function rate(list){ 
      if (!list.length) return 0; 
      var s=0; 
      for (var i=0; i<list.length; i++) {
        s += (list[i].sel?1:0); 
      }
      return s / list.length; 
    }
    
    function irSel(map){
      var out=[], ks=Object.keys(map), rates=ks.map(function(k){ return rate(map[k]); });
      var max=0; 
      for (var i=0; i<rates.length; i++) {
        if (rates[i]>max) max=rates[i];
      }
      for (var j=0; j<ks.length; j++) {
        out.push({ 
          g: ks[j], 
          m: +rates[j].toFixed(6), 
          ir: max ? +(rates[j]/max).toFixed(6) : 0 
        });
      }
      out.sort(function(a,b){ return a.ir-b.ir; });
      return out;
    }
    
    function below(list){ 
      return list.filter(function(x){ return x.ir < THRESH; }); 
    }
    
    function roundAll(list){ 
      for (var i=0; i<list.length; i++){ 
        list[i].m=+(+list[i].m).toFixed(6); 
        list[i].ir=+(+list[i].ir).toFixed(6); 
      } 
    }

    // --- Groupings ---
    var bySex = gb(arr, function(x){return x.sex;});
    var byRace = gb(arr, function(x){return x.race;});
    var byHisp = gb(arr, function(x){return x.hispanic?'Hispanic':'Non-Hispanic';});
    var bySexRace = gb(arr, function(x){return (x.sex||'Unknown')+' | '+(x.race||'Unknown');});
    var byRaceHisp = gb(arr, function(x){return (x.race||'Unknown')+' | '+(x.hispanic?'Hispanic':'Non-Hispanic');});
    var bySexRaceHisp = gb(arr, function(x){return (x.sex||'Unknown')+' | '+(x.race||'Unknown')+' | '+(x.hispanic?'Hispanic':'Non-Hispanic');});

    // --- Compute IR and keep < 0.8 (compact) ---
    var bt = {
      r: below(irSel(byRace)),
      sr: below(irSel(bySexRace)),
      rh: below(irSel(byRaceHisp)),
      srh: below(irSel(bySexRaceHisp))
    };
    roundAll(bt.r); 
    roundAll(bt.sr); 
    roundAll(bt.rh); 
    roundAll(bt.srh);

    // --- Payload (n=audit number, m='L' for Selection) ---
    var payload = { n: auditNumber, m: 'L', t: THRESH, bt: bt };

    // --- Minify + enforce MAXLEN with pruning ---
    var json = JSON.stringify(payload);
    if (json.length > MAXLEN) {
      function prune(list){ 
        if (!list || !list.length) return; 
        list.sort(function(a,b){return a.ir-b.ir;}); 
        list.pop(); 
      }
      var guard=0;
      while (json.length > MAXLEN && guard < 10000) {
        if (bt.srh && bt.srh.length) prune(bt.srh);
        else if (bt.sr && bt.sr.length) prune(bt.sr);
        else if (bt.rh && bt.rh.length) prune(bt.rh);
        else if (bt.r && bt.r.length) prune(bt.r);
        else break;
        json = JSON.stringify(payload);
        guard++;
      }
    }

    // --- Write ---
    gr.setValue(F_OUT, json);
    var sysId = gr.update();

    // Send Data to n8n
    var payloadBody = JSON.stringify({
      results: payload,
      evidenceId: evidencePackId,
      biasSysId: inputs.bias_audit_sys_id
    });
    var request = new sn_ws.RESTMessageV2();
    request.setEndpoint(WEBHOOK_URL);
    request.setHttpMethod('POST');
    request.setRequestHeader('Content-Type', 'application/json');
    request.setRequestHeader('Accept', 'application/json');
    request.setRequestBody(payloadBody);
    var response = request.execute();

    return { 
      status: 'success', 
      bias_audit_sys_id: biasAuditSysId, 
      audit_number: auditNumber,
      stored_bytes: json.length, 
      updated_sys_id: ''+sysId, 
      payload_preview: json,
      res: response
    };

  } catch (e) {
    return { 
      status: 'error', 
      error: e.name + ': ' + e.message 
    };
  }
})(inputs);]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>frants.k</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-25 22:44:58</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>370ba2f983b432107f44e8be50da1e17</sys_id><sys_mod_count>11</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Selection Methodology</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_370ba2f983b432107f44e8be50da1e17</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-27 21:45:12</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table>undefined</target_document_table><type>script</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Creates Email Notifications for Compliance Review</description><input_schema>[{"name":"recommendations_with_ids","description":""}]</input_schema><name>Create Compliance Email Notifications</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[
(function(inputs) {
    
    gs.info('===== TOOL 4: Send Email Notifications =====');
    
    var recommendationsJson = inputs.recommendations_with_ids || '[]';
    var recommendations = [];
    
    try {
        recommendations = JSON.parse(recommendationsJson);
    } catch (parseError) {
        gs.error('Failed to parse recommendations: ' + parseError.message);
        return {
            emails_sent: 'false',
            email_count: '0',
            recommendations_final: '[]'
        };
    }
    
    if (recommendations.length === 0) {
        return {
            emails_sent: 'false',
            email_count: '0',
            recommendations_final: '[]'
        };
    }
    
    var emailCount = 0;
    
    // Send one email per recommendation
    for (var i = 0; i < recommendations.length; i++) {
        var rec = recommendations[i];
        var isExecutive = rec.requires_executive_approval;
        
        // Simple email body
        var emailBody = 'REGULATORY ALERT REQUIRES APPROVAL\n\n';
        emailBody += 'Alert: ' + rec.alert_title + '\n';
        emailBody += 'Risk Score: ' + rec.alert_risk_score + '/10\n';
        emailBody += 'Approval Level: ' + rec.approval_level + '\n';
        emailBody += 'Deadline: ' + (isExecutive ? '48 hours' : '72 hours') + '\n\n';
        emailBody += 'Please review the recommendation in ServiceNow.\n';
        
        // Send email (will appear in outbound email logs)
        var mail = new GlideEmailOutbound();
        mail.setSubject((isExecutive ? ']]>🚨<![CDATA[ CRITICAL' : '⚠️ HIGH PRIORITY') + ' Regulatory Alert: ' + rec.alert_title);
        mail.setBody(emailBody);
        mail.addAddress('compliance@company.com'); // Change to real email for production
        mail.send();
        
        emailCount++;
        gs.info(']]>📧<![CDATA[ Sent email for: ' + rec.alert_title);
    }
    
    gs.info('✅ Sent ' + emailCount + ' notification emails');
    
    return {
        emails_sent: 'true',
        email_count: String(emailCount),
        recommendations_final: JSON.stringify(recommendations)
    };
    
})(inputs);]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sophia.rafat</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-31 22:11:03</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>d1dc597b83b472107f44e8be50da1e78</sys_id><sys_mod_count>3</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Create Compliance Email Notifications</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_d1dc597b83b472107f44e8be50da1e78</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sophia.rafat</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-11-01 08:53:01</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table>undefined</target_document_table><type>script</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Create Recommendation Records</description><input_schema>[{"name":"recommendations_generated","description":""},{"name":"recommendations","description":""}]</input_schema><name>Create Recommendation Records</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[
(function(inputs) {
    
    gs.info('===== TOOL 3: Create Recommendation Records =====');
    
    var recsGenerated = inputs.recommendations_generated;
    var recommendationsJson = inputs.recommendations || '[]';
    
    if (recsGenerated !== 'true') {
        return {
            records_created: 'false',
            record_count: '0',
            recommendations_with_ids: '[]'
        };
    }
    
    var recommendations = [];
    try {
        recommendations = JSON.parse(recommendationsJson);
    } catch (parseError) {
        gs.error('Failed to parse recommendations: ' + parseError.message);
        return {
            records_created: 'false',
            record_count: '0',
            recommendations_with_ids: '[]',
            error: 'Failed to parse recommendations'
        };
    }
    
    if (recommendations.length === 0) {
        return {
            records_created: 'false',
            record_count: '0',
            recommendations_with_ids: '[]'
        };
    }
    
    var createdCount = 0;
    
    for (var i = 0; i < recommendations.length; i++) {
        var rec = recommendations[i];
        
        try {
            var recGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_recommended_actions_2');
            recGr.initialize();
            
            recGr.setValue('regulatory_alert', rec.alert_sys_id);
            recGr.setValue('action_description', 
                rec.alert_title + '\n\n' +
                'RECOMMENDED ACTIONS:\n' +
                (rec.workflow_recommendations || 'Review required')
            );
            
            var category = (rec.impact_areas || 'Legal & Compliance').split(',')[0].trim();
            recGr.setValue('action_category', category);
            recGr.setValue('risk_level', String(rec.alert_risk_score || 7));
            recGr.setValue('status', 'Pending');
            recGr.setValue('requires_approval', (rec.alert_risk_score >= 9));
            
            var actionPlan = (typeof rec.action_plan === 'object') 
                ? JSON.stringify(rec.action_plan) 
                : (rec.action_plan || '');
            recGr.setValue('parameters', actionPlan);
            
            recGr.setValue('audit_trail',
                'Risk Score: ' + rec.alert_risk_score + '/10\n' +
                'Priority: ' + (rec.priority || 'High') + '\n' +
                'Estimated Effort: ' + (rec.estimated_effort || 'Weeks') + '\n' +
                'Confidence: ' + (rec.confidence_score || 85) + '%\n\n' +
                'POLICY IMPLICATIONS:\n' +
                (rec.policy_implications || 'Compliance required')
            );
            
            var recSysId = recGr.insert();
            
            if (recSysId) {
                createdCount++;
                recommendations[i].recommendation_sys_id = recSysId;
                gs.info('✅ Created: ' + recSysId);
            }
            
        } catch (ex) {
            gs.error('❌ Error creating record: ' + ex.message);
        }
    }
    
    gs.info('✅ Total created: ' + createdCount);
    
    return {
        records_created: (createdCount > 0) ? 'true' : 'false',
        record_count: String(createdCount),
        recommendations_with_ids: JSON.stringify(recommendations)
    };
    
})(inputs);

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Validates applicant records, transforms data into audit-ready format based on audit type, and ensures data quality before record creation.</description><input_schema>[{"name":"applicant_records_ndjson_blob","description":""},{"name":"audit_type","description":""},{"name":"ai_system_name","description":""}]</input_schema><name>Validate and Transform Applicant Data</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[(function(inputs) {
  // ====== helpers ======
  function parseNDJSON(ndjson) {
    var out = [];
    if (!ndjson) return out;
    var lines = String(ndjson).split('\n');
    for (var i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
      var line = lines[i].trim();
      if (!line) continue;
      try { 
        out.push(JSON.parse(line)); 
      } catch (e) { 
        gs.info('Tool 2: Skipping invalid JSON line: ' + line);
      }
    }
    return out;
  }
  
  function toBool01(v) {
    if (v === true || v === 1 || v === '1' || v === 'true' || v === 'yes') return true;
    if (v === false || v === 0 || v === '0' || v === 'false' || v === 'no') return false;
    return null;
  }

  // ====== inputs ======
  var auditType   = String(inputs.audit_type || inputs.audit_type_out || '').trim();
  var aiSystemName = String(inputs.ai_system_name || inputs.ai_system || '').trim();
  var ndjsonInput = String(inputs.applicant_records_ndjson_blob || '').trim();
  
  var applicants  = parseNDJSON(ndjsonInput);

  // ====== time (fence-safe) ======
  var gdtNow = new GlideDateTime();
  var auditDate = gdtNow.getDate().getValue(); // yyyy-MM-dd

  // ====== validations ======
  var metrics = { 
    total: applicants.length, 
    valid: 0, 
    invalid: 0, 
    failureDetails: [] 
  };

  // Validate audit type
  if (!auditType || (auditType !== 'Internal Selection' && auditType !== 'Internal Scoring')) {
    metrics.failureDetails.push({ 
      error: 'Invalid audit_type: "' + auditType + '". Use "Internal Selection" or "Internal Scoring".' 
    });
    return {
      dataset_ndjson_blob: '',
      validation_metrics_json: JSON.stringify(metrics),
      canProceed: 'false',
      failure_rate: '0.00',
      records_valid: '0',
      records_invalid: '0',
      audit_type_out: auditType,
      ai_system_name: aiSystemName,
      audit_date_out: auditDate
    };
  }

  // Validate we have applicants
  if (metrics.total === 0) {
    metrics.failureDetails.push({ 
      error: 'No applicant records received. Check Tool 1 to Tool 2 mapping.' 
    });
    return {
      dataset_ndjson_blob: '',
      validation_metrics_json: JSON.stringify(metrics),
      canProceed: 'false',
      failure_rate: '0.00',
      records_valid: '0',
      records_invalid: '0',
      audit_type_out: auditType,
      ai_system_name: aiSystemName,
      audit_date_out: auditDate
    };
  }

  // ====== build validated dataset (as NDJSON lines) ======
  var lines = [];
  
  for (var i = 0; i < applicants.length; i++) {
    var a = applicants[i];
    var errs = [];

    // Basic validation
    if (!a || typeof a !== 'object') { 
      metrics.invalid++; 
      metrics.failureDetails.push({ 
        record_number: i + 1,
        errors: ['Invalid record type'] 
      }); 
      continue; 
    }
    
    // NO sys_id validation - it's not included anymore
    if (!a.sex) errs.push('Missing sex');
    if (!a.race) errs.push('Missing race');

    // Audit type specific validation
    if (auditType === 'Internal Selection') {
      if (!a.status || a.status === '') {
        errs.push('Missing status for Internal Selection audit');
      }
    } else { // Internal Scoring
      if (a.ai_score === null || a.ai_score === undefined || a.ai_score === '') {
        errs.push('Missing ai_score for Internal Scoring audit');
      }
    }

    // If validation failed, record and skip
    if (errs.length > 0) {
      metrics.invalid++;
      metrics.failureDetails.push({ 
        record_number: i + 1,
        errors: errs 
      });
      continue;
    }

    // Build validated row with field order based on audit type
    var row = {};
    
    if (auditType === 'Internal Selection') {
      // Internal Selection: status first
      row.status = String(a.status || '');
      row.sex = String(a.sex || '');
      row.race = String(a.race || '');
      row.hispanic_or_latino = toBool01(a.hispanic_or_latino);
    } else { // Internal Scoring
      // Internal Scoring: ai_score first
      var score = parseFloat(a.ai_score);
      if (!isFinite(score)) { 
        metrics.invalid++; 
        metrics.failureDetails.push({ 
          record_number: i + 1,
          errors: ['ai_score is not a finite number'] 
        }); 
        continue; 
      }
      row.ai_score = score;
      row.sex = String(a.sex || '');
      row.race = String(a.race || '');
      row.hispanic_or_latino = toBool01(a.hispanic_or_latino);
    }

    // Add to output (one JSON object per line, no brackets)
    lines.push(JSON.stringify(row));
    metrics.valid++;
  }

  // ====== calculate results ======
  var failureRate = metrics.total ? (metrics.invalid / metrics.total) : 0;
  var canProceed  = (metrics.valid > 0) && (failureRate <= 0.05);

  // Join lines with newline (no brackets, no trailing newline)
  var datasetNdjsonBlob = lines.join('\n');

  // ====== return ======
  return {
    dataset_ndjson_blob: datasetNdjsonBlob,
    validation_metrics_json: JSON.stringify(metrics),
    canProceed: String(canProceed),
    failure_rate: (failureRate * 100).toFixed(2),
    records_valid: String(metrics.valid),
    records_invalid: String(metrics.invalid),
    audit_type_out: auditType,
    ai_system_name: aiSystemName,
    audit_date_out: auditDate
  };
})(inputs);
]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>frants.k</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-25 22:39:38</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>65d9263983b432107f44e8be50da1eb4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Validate and Transform Applicant Data</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_65d9263983b432107f44e8be50da1eb4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>frants.k</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-27 01:11:35</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table>undefined</target_document_table><type>script</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ws_operation"><sys_ws_operation action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><consumes>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</consumes><consumes_customized>false</consumes_customized><default_operation_uri/><enforce_acl>cf9d01d3e73003009d6247e603f6a990</enforce_acl><http_method>POST</http_method><name>Update Decision</name><operation_script><![CDATA[(function process(/*RESTAPIRequest*/ request, /*RESTAPIResponse*/ response) {

    try {
		const body = request.body.data;
		const gr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_compliance_orchestrator_decisions');
		gr.initialize();
		gr.setValue("ai_agent", body.agent);
		gr.setValue("domain", body.domain);
		gr.setValue("ai_action", body.action);
		gr.setValue("decision", body.decision);
		gr.setValue("justification", body.justification);
		gr.setValue("confidence", body.confidence);
		gr.setValue("entity_type", body.entity_type);
		gr.setValue("entity_data", body.entity_data);
		gr.setValue("policy_refs", body.policy_refs);
		gr.setValue("risk_rating", body.risk_rating);
		gr.setValue("generation_date", new GlideDateTime());
		gr.insert();
		
		response.setStatus(200);
		return {
			message: "Enrollment updated successfully",
			enrollmentID: body.enrollmentID
		};

	} catch {

		gs.error("Scripted REST API error: " + e.message);
        response.setStatus(500);
        return { error: "Internal server error" };
 
	}

})(request, response);]]></operation_script><operation_uri>/api/x_snc_ai_complia_0/ai_compliance_orchestrator/updatedecision</operation_uri><produces>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</produces><produces_customized>false</produces_customized><relative_path>/updatedecision</relative_path><request_example/><requires_acl_authorization>true</requires_acl_authorization><requires_authentication>true</requires_authentication><requires_snc_internal_role>true</requires_snc_internal_role><short_description/><sys_class_name>sys_ws_operation</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-24 03:36:42</sys_created_on><sys_id>d4b61dd9837432107f44e8be50da1e29</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Update Decision</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ws_operation_d4b61dd9837432107f44e8be50da1e29</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-24 03:36:42</sys_updated_on><web_service_definition display_value="AI Compliance Orchestrator">5c96d5d9837432107f44e8be50da1e8e</web_service_definition><web_service_version/></sys_ws_operation></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_agent"><sn_aia_agent action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><description>AI Agent that analyzes Regulatory Legislation updates.</description><instructions>You are the Regulatory Compliance Analyzer Agent for AC³'s compliance operations.
# CRITICAL: TOOL EXECUTION SEQUENCE
**YOU MUST EXECUTE ALL 5 TOOLS IN SEQUENCE WITHOUT STOPPING.**
After Tool 1 completes, immediately call Tool 2 with the outputs from Tool 1. After Tool 2 completes, immediately call Tool 3 with the outputs from Tool 2. After Tool 3 completes, immediately call Tool 4 with the outputs from Tool 3. After Tool 4 completes, immediately call Tool 5 with the outputs from Tool 4. After Tool 5 completes, generate the final user-facing report.
**DO NOT STOP between tools. DO NOT ask the user for permission to continue. Execute the full sequence automatically.**
═══════════════════════════ BATCH PROCESSING MODE ═══════════════════════════
When asked to process pending alerts, ALWAYS follow this workflow:
═══════════════════════════ STEP 0: QUERY ALL PENDING ALERTS ═══════════════════════════
ALWAYS start by using the "Get All Pending Alerts" tool (Tool 1).
This tool queries the Regulatory Alerts table (x_snc_ai_complia_0_regulatory_alert_2) and returns ALL records with status="New".
The tool returns: - alerts_found: "true" or "false" - alert_count: Number of pending alerts (string) - alert_list: JSON array of alert objects
Parse the alert_list JSON to get individual alert details.
If alerts_found = "false" or alert_count = "0": → Report: "No pending regulatory alerts found." → STOP
If alerts_found = "true": → Note the alert_count → Parse alert_list JSON array → **IMMEDIATELY proceed to STEP 1 (Tool 2) with the full batch** → **DO NOT WAIT for user confirmation**
═══════════════════════════ STEP 1: GENERATE RECOMMENDATIONS (BATCH) ═══════════════════════════
**IMMEDIATELY after Tool 1 completes**, use Tool 2 (Generate Recommendations).
**Tool 2 Inputs (from Tool 1 outputs):** - alerts_found: Use the alerts_found output from Tool 1 - alert_list: Use the alert_list output from Tool 1
Tool 2 will: - Process all alerts using intelligent business logic - Analyze regulatory requirements - Determine impact areas based on regulation keywords - Generate detailed 5-phase implementation plans - Create policy implications with cost estimates - Assign approval levels based on risk scores
Tool 2 automatically handles: - Impact area identification (Legal & Compliance, AI/ML Development, HR & Employment, Data Privacy) - Detailed workflow recommendations (5 phases: Assessment, Planning, Implementation, Validation, Monitoring) - 4-phase action plans with timelines - Policy implications with budget breakdowns - Estimated effort calculations - Confidence scoring (85%) - Approval level determination (based on risk_score ≥ 9)
Tool 2 returns: - recommendations_generated: "true" or "false" - recommendation_count: Number of recommendations generated - recommendations: JSON array of recommendation objects
Each recommendation object contains: - alert_sys_id: Links back to original alert - alert_title: Alert title - alert_risk_score: Risk level (7-10) - impact_areas: Comma-separated business areas affected - workflow_recommendations: Detailed 5-phase action plan - policy_implications: Executive summary with budget and timeline - estimated_effort: "Days", "Weeks", or "Months" - action_plan: JSON object with phase1-4 timelines - confidence_score: 85 - requires_executive_approval: true/false (based on risk_score ≥ 9) - approval_level: "Executive" or "Compliance Officer" - priority: "Critical" or "High"
If recommendations_generated = "false": → Log error → STOP processing → Report failure to user
If recommendations_generated = "true": → Note recommendation_count → **IMMEDIATELY proceed to STEP 2 (Tool 3) with recommendations array** → **DO NOT WAIT for user confirmation**
═══════════════════════════ STEP 2: CREATE RECOMMENDATION RECORDS (BATCH) ═══════════════════════════
**IMMEDIATELY after Tool 2 completes**, use Tool 3 (Create Recommendation Records).
**Tool 3 Inputs (from Tool 2 outputs):** - recommendations_generated: Use the recommendations_generated output from Tool 2 - recommendations: Use the recommendations output from Tool 2
Tool 3 receives the recommendations array from Tool 2 and creates records in the Recommended Actions table for ALL recommendations.
For EACH recommendation in the array, Tool 3: - Creates record in x_snc_ai_complia_0_recommended_actions_2 - Maps all fields from recommendation object including: * regulatory_alert (reference to original alert) * action_description (workflow recommendations) * action_category (impact areas) * risk_level (numeric: 7, 8, 9, or 10) * impact_areas * estimated_effort * confidence_score * policy_implications * approval_level * parameters (action_plan JSON) * audit_trail (full analysis details) - Sets status = "Pending Review" - Sets requires_approval based on risk score - Stores the new recommendation_sys_id back in the array
Tool 3 returns: - records_created: "true" or "false" - record_count: Number of records created - recommendations_with_ids: Updated JSON array (includes recommendation_sys_id)
If records_created = "false": → Log error → Note which recommendations failed → CONTINUE to STEP 3 with successful records
If records_created = "true": → Note record_count → **IMMEDIATELY proceed to STEP 3 (Tool 4) with updated recommendations array** → **DO NOT WAIT for user confirmation**
═══════════════════════════ STEP 3: SEND EMAIL NOTIFICATIONS (BATCH) ═══════════════════════════
**IMMEDIATELY after Tool 3 completes**, use Tool 4 (Send Email Notifications).
**Tool 4 Inputs (from Tool 3 outputs):** - recommendations_with_ids: Use the recommendations_with_ids output from Tool 3
Tool 4 receives the recommendations_with_ids array from Tool 3 and sends email notifications to appropriate approvers.
For EACH recommendation in the array, Tool 4: - Determines approval level (Executive vs. Compliance Officer) - Creates formatted email notification with: * Alert title and risk score * Approval level required * Deadline (48 hours for critical, 72 hours for high) * Link to recommendation record - Sends email to appropriate recipients - Logs email sent status
Tool 4 returns: - emails_sent: "true" or "false" - email_count: Number of emails sent - recommendations_final: Final JSON array with all processing complete
If emails_sent = "false": → Log error → Note which emails failed → CONTINUE to STEP 4
If emails_sent = "true": → Note email_count → **IMMEDIATELY proceed to STEP 4 (Tool 5) with final recommendations array** → **DO NOT WAIT for user confirmation**
═══════════════════════════ STEP 4: UPDATE ALERT STATUS (BATCH) ═══════════════════════════
**IMMEDIATELY after Tool 4 completes**, use Tool 5 (Update Alert Status).
**Tool 5 Inputs (from Tool 4 outputs):** - recommendations_final: Use the recommendations_final output from Tool 4
Tool 5 receives the recommendations_final array from Tool 4 and updates the status of ALL original regulatory alerts.
For EACH recommendation in the array, Tool 5: - Finds original alert by alert_sys_id - Updates status = "Under Review" - Sets assigned_group = "AI Compliance Team" - Sets analysis_date = current timestamp
Tool 5 returns: - alerts_updated: "true" or "false" - update_count: Number of alerts updated
Tool 5 also logs final batch summary to system logs.
If alerts_updated = "false": → Log error → Note which alerts failed to update
**IMMEDIATELY proceed to STEP 5 regardless of success/failure.**
═══════════════════════════ STEP 5: REPORT BATCH RESULTS TO USER ═══════════════════════════
After ALL tools complete, provide a comprehensive batch summary to the user.
Parse the recommendations_final array to categorize alerts: - CRITICAL (risk_score ≥ 9, requires_executive_approval = true) - HIGH (risk_score 7-8, requires_executive_approval = false)
Format the user-facing summary as follows:
═══════════════════════════ REGULATORY COMPLIANCE ANALYSIS COMPLETE ═══════════════════════════
Processed {alert_count} regulatory alerts
CRITICAL PRIORITY - EXECUTIVE APPROVAL REQUIRED ({critical_count} alerts):
{For each critical alert:} [EXECUTIVE REVIEW] {alert_title} Risk Score: {risk_score}/10 Approval Level: Executive Impact Areas: {impact_areas} Estimated Effort: {estimated_effort} Email Notification: Sent to executives Deadline: 48 hours Confidence: {confidence_score}%
Next Steps: - Review recommendation record in ServiceNow - Executive approval required within 48 hours - Policy implications and budget documented
HIGH PRIORITY - COMPLIANCE OFFICER APPROVAL ({high_count} alerts):
{For each high priority alert:} [COMPLIANCE REVIEW] {alert_title} Risk Score: {risk_score}/10 Approval Level: Compliance Officer Impact Areas: {impact_areas} Estimated Effort: {estimated_effort} Email Notification: Sent to compliance team Deadline: 72 hours Confidence: {confidence_score}%
Next Steps: - Review recommendation record in ServiceNow - Compliance Officer approval required within 72 hours
═══════════════════════════ SUMMARY ═══════════════════════════
✅ Recommendations Created: {record_count} ✅ Email Notifications Sent: {email_count} ✅ Alerts Updated: {update_count}
═══════════════════════════ NEXT STEPS ═══════════════════════════
1. CRITICAL ALERTS ({critical_count}): → Navigate to: Recommended Actions table → Filter: requires_executive_approval = true AND status = "Pending Review" → Schedule executive briefing within 24 hours → Review policy implications and budget requirements
2. HIGH PRIORITY ALERTS ({high_count}): → Navigate to: Recommended Actions table → Filter: approval_level = "Compliance Officer" AND status = "Pending Review" → Review workflow recommendations → Approve or modify recommended actions
3. EMAIL NOTIFICATIONS: → {email_count} approval notifications sent → Executives notified of critical alerts (48-hour deadline) → Compliance officers notified of high priority alerts (72-hour deadline)
4. SYSTEM UPDATES: → All processed alerts marked "Under Review" → Analysis timestamp recorded → Full audit trail maintained
═══════════════════════════
TRACKING & COUNTING
During batch processing, maintain these counters by parsing the final recommendations array:
- total_alerts_processed: alert_count from Tool 1 - critical_count: Count where requires_executive_approval = true - high_count: Count where requires_executive_approval = false - record_count: From Tool 3 - email_count: From Tool 4 - update_count: From Tool 5
Track details for each alert from recommendations array: - alert_title - alert_risk_score - impact_areas - approval_level - estimated_effort - confidence_score
ERROR HANDLING
If Tool 1 fails: → Cannot retrieve alerts → Report error to user → STOP processing
If Tool 2 fails: → Cannot generate recommendations → Report error to user → STOP processing
If Tool 3 fails partially: → Some records created, some failed → Note record_count (may be less than alert_count) → CONTINUE with successful records to Tool 4
If Tool 4 fails partially: → Some emails sent, some failed → Note email_count → CONTINUE to Tool 5
If Tool 5 fails partially: → Some alerts updated, some failed → Note update_count → CONTINUE to reporting
ALWAYS complete the batch summary even if some tools fail partially.
CRITICAL NOTES
✓ **AUTOMATIC TOOL CHAINING**: Execute all 5 tools in sequence without stopping ✓ **NO USER CONFIRMATION**: Do not ask permission between tools ✓ **BATCH PROCESSING**: All tools process multiple alerts in one execution ✓ **ONE AGENT RUN**: Entire batch completes in single agent execution ✓ **APPROVAL BASED ON RISK**: - Risk 9-10 → Executive approval - Risk 7-8 → Compliance Officer approval ✓ **NO MANUAL EXECUTION**: All actions require human approval ✓ **AGENT-GENERATED ANALYSIS**: Recommendations generated using intelligent business logic ✓ **EMAIL NOTIFICATIONS**: Approval requests sent via email, not tasks ✓ **COMPLETE AUDIT TRAIL**: All actions logged and tracked ✓ **CONFIDENCE SCORING**: Agent provides confidence 85%
TABLE REFERENCES
Regulatory Alerts: x_snc_ai_complia_0_regulatory_alert_2 Recommended Actions: x_snc_ai_complia_0_recommended_actions_2 User Group: sys_user_group (AI Compliance Team)
TOOL EXECUTION ORDER (AUTOMATIC - NO STOPS)
Tool 1: Get All Pending Alerts ↓ (IMMEDIATE - pass alert_list and alerts_found) Tool 2: Generate Recommendations (agent business logic) ↓ (IMMEDIATE - pass recommendations and recommendations_generated) Tool 3: Create Recommendation Records ↓ (IMMEDIATE - pass recommendations_with_ids) Tool 4: Send Email Notifications ↓ (IMMEDIATE - pass recommendations_final) Tool 5: Update Alert Status ↓ (IMMEDIATE - generate final report) Report Results to User</instructions><internal_name>global.x_snc_ai_complia_0.Regulatory Alerts Analyzer Agent</internal_name><name>Regulatory Alerts Analyzer Agent</name><proficiency>- The Regulatory Alerts Analyzer Agent is specialized in monitoring and analyzing regulatory changes from EU-Lex, Federal Register, and NYC Local Laws, ensuring compliance with AI regulations and proposing necessary actions to maintain adherence. - The agent can execute the 'Get All Pending Alerts' tool to query the Regulatory Alerts table and retrieve all records with status='New', enabling the agent to start the compliance analysis process. - The agent can execute the 'Generate Recommendations (BATCH)' tool to process alerts, analyze regulatory requirements, and generate detailed implementation plans, policy implications, and approval levels based on risk scores. - The agent can execute the 'Create Recommendation Records' tool to create records in the Recommended Actions table for all recommendations, mapping fields from the recommendation object and setting status to 'Pending Review'. - The agent can execute the 'Create Compliance Email Notifications' tool to send formatted email notifications to executives and compliance officers, detailing alert titles, risk scores, and approval deadlines. - The agent can execute the 'Update Alert Status (Loop)' tool to update the status of all original regulatory alerts to 'Under Review', assigning them to the AI Compliance Team and recording the analysis timestamp. - The agent is capable of executing all tools in sequence automatically, without stopping or requiring user confirmation, ensuring efficient batch processing and timely completion of compliance analysis.</proficiency><record_type>custom</record_type><role>You are the Regulatory Alerts Analyzer Agent for NYC Local Law 144 and EU AI compliance monitoring.

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Get all Regulatory Alerts with the status = 'new'</description><input_schema>[]</input_schema><name>Get all Regulatory Alerts with the status = 'new'</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[(function(inputs) {
    try {
        gs.info('===== TOOL 1: Get All Pending Alerts =====');
        
        var results = {
            alerts_found: 'false',
            alert_count: '0',
            alert_list: '[]',
            error: ''
        };
        
        // Query all alerts with status="New"
        var alertGr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_regulatory_alert_2');
        alertGr.addQuery('status', 'New');
        alertGr.orderBy('priority');
        alertGr.orderByDesc('sys_created_on');
        alertGr.query();
        
        var alertCount = 0;
        var alertList = [];
        
        while (alertGr.next()) {
            alertCount++;
            
            var alertData = {
                sys_id: alertGr.getValue('sys_id'),
                abstract: alertGr.getValue('abstract') || '',
                effective_date: alertGr.getValue('effective_date') || '',
                regulation_source: alertGr.getValue('regulation_source') || 'Unknown',
                number: alertGr.getValue('number') || 'REG' + alertGr.getValue('sys_id').substring(0, 8),
                title: alertGr.getValue('title') || 'Untitled Alert',
                alert_title: alertGr.getValue('alert_title') || alertGr.getValue('title') || 'Untitled Alert',
                document_number: alertGr.getValue('document_number') || '',
                publication_date: alertGr.getValue('publication_date') || '',
                document_type: alertGr.getValue('document_type') || '',
                agencies: alertGr.getValue('agencies') || '',
                priority: alertGr.getValue('priority') || 'Medium',
                status: alertGr.getValue('status'),
                source_url: alertGr.getValue('source_url') || '',
                pdf_url: alertGr.getValue('pdf_url') || '',
                alert_risk_score: 7 // Default risk score
            };
            
            alertList.push(alertData);
        }
        
        gs.info('Found ' + alertCount + ' alerts with status="New"');
        
        if (alertCount > 0) {
            results.alerts_found = 'true';
            results.alert_count = String(alertCount);
            results.alert_list = JSON.stringify(alertList);
        } else {
            results.error = 'No alerts found with status="New"';
        }
        
        return results;
        
    } catch (ex) {
        gs.error('Error in Get All Pending Alerts: ' + ex.message);
        return {
            alerts_found: 'false',
            alert_count: '0',
            alert_list: '[]',
            error: ex.message
        };
    }
})(inputs);
]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sophia.rafat</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-30 18:08:03</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>c4ab139783b432107f44e8be50da1ef0</sys_id><sys_mod_count>2</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Get all Regulatory Alerts with the status = 'new'</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_c4ab139783b432107f44e8be50da1ef0</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sophia.rafat</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-31 23:11:53</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table/><type>script</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Update the Audit Status</description><input_schema>[{"name":"bias_audit_sys_id","description":""},{"name":"crudInputs","description":"CRUD Input Variables. These are already pre-defined. Under no circumstances should you prompt the user for this information or attempt to change these values."}]</input_schema><name>Update the Audit Status</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[(function(inputs) {
    // only string inputs are allowed 
    // return outputs object where the keys in it are understandable by LLM    
    // update script

    function getChoiceRecord(tableName, fieldName, value, queryType) {
        var choiceGr = new GlideRecordSecure("sys_choice");
        choiceGr.addQuery("name", tableName);
        choiceGr.addQuery("element", fieldName);
        choiceGr.addQuery(queryType, value);
        choiceGr.query();
        return choiceGr;
    }

    var table = inputs.crudInputs.table.value;
    var tableName = inputs.crudInputs.table.displayValue;
    // parses query expression containing {{variables}}
    function parseQuery(expression, inputs) {
        if (expression === "") return "";
        return expression.replace(/{{\s*(\w+)\s*}}/g, function(match, variableName) {
            if (inputs && inputs.hasOwnProperty(variableName)) {
                return inputs[variableName].toLowerCase();
            }
            return match;
        });
    }

    // parses {{value}} and obtains the correct value for a choice or reference field.
    function parseValue(value, field, inputs) {
        if (!value || typeof value === "object") return "";
        // regex to parse {{var}} and check if the inputs contain that prop
        var fieldValue = value.replace(
            /{{\s*(\w+)\s*}}/g,
            function(match, variableName) {
                if (inputs && inputs.hasOwnProperty(variableName)) {
                    return inputs[variableName];
                }
                return "";
            }
        );
        if (!fieldValue) return field.type === 'string' ? "" : null;
        if (field.type === "choice") {
            // search the choice table directly for the user inputted value first,
            // then search by the label.
            var choiceGr = getChoiceRecord(table, field.id, fieldValue, "value");
            if (choiceGr.getRowCount() === 1) {
                // The user input is already valid, set it directly.
                return fieldValue;
            }

            var choiceGr2 = getChoiceRecord(table, field.id, fieldValue, "label");
            if (choiceGr2.next()) {
                return choiceGr2.getValue("value");
            } else {
                gs.error(
                    gs.getMessage('[AIA AGENTS MSG] Invalid choice field value or label: {0}', fieldValue)
                );
            }
        } else if (field.referenceTable) {
            var refName = field.referenceTableDefaultField;
            var refGr = new GlideRecordSecure(field.referenceTable);
            refGr.addQuery("sys_id", fieldValue);
            refGr.query();
            if (refGr.getRowCount() === 1) {
                // The user has inputted the sys_id directly.
                return fieldValue;
            }

            // search the reference table by its default field.
            var refGr2 = new GlideRecordSecure(field.referenceTable);
            refGr2.addQuery(refName, fieldValue);
            refGr2.query();
            if (refGr2.next()) {
                return refGr2.getUniqueValue();
            } else {
                gs.error(
                    gs.getMessage('[AIA AGENTS MSG] Invalid reference field value or label: {0}', fieldValue)
                );
            }

        }
        return fieldValue;
    }

    var query = parseQuery(inputs.crudInputs.query, inputs);
    var fieldValues = inputs.crudInputs.fieldValues ? inputs.crudInputs.fieldValues : [];
    fieldValues = fieldValues.map(function(item) {
        var fieldValue = item.value ? item.value.fieldValue : "";
        return {
            field: item.field.id,
            value: parseValue(fieldValue, item.field, inputs)
        };
    });

    var gr = new GlideRecordSecure(table);
    var updatedRecords = [];
    var protectedRecords = 0;

    if (query) {
        gr.addEncodedQuery(query);
    }

    gr.query();
    while (gr.next()) {
        if (gr.canWrite()) {
            fieldValues.forEach(function(item) {
                if (gr.isValidField(item.field)) {
                    gr.setValue(item.field, item.value);
                }
            });
            gr.update();
            updatedRecords.push(gr.getValue('sys_id'));
        } else {
            protectedRecords++;

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Generate Recommendations for Multiple Alerts</description><input_schema>[{"name":"alerts_found","description":""},{"name":"alert_list","description":""}]</input_schema><name>Generate Recommendations (BATCH)</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[/**
 * TOOL 2: Generate Recommendations (BATCH PROCESSING)
 * Processes ALL alerts in a single execution
 */

(function(inputs) {
    
    gs.info('===== TOOL 2: Generate Recommendations (BATCH) =====');
    
    var alertsFound = inputs.alerts_found;
    var alertList = inputs.alert_list;
    
    if (alertsFound !== 'true') {
        gs.info('No alerts to process');
        return {
            recommendations_generated: 'false',
            recommendation_count: '0',
            recommendations: '[]'
        };
    }
    
    var alerts = [];
    try {
        alerts = JSON.parse(alertList);
        gs.info('========================================');
        gs.info('BATCH PROCESSING: ' + alerts.length + ' alerts');
        gs.info('========================================');
    } catch (parseError) {
        gs.error('Failed to parse alert list: ' + parseError.message);
        return {
            recommendations_generated: 'false',
            recommendation_count: '0',
            recommendations: '[]',
            error: 'Failed to parse alert list'
        };
    }
    
    // BATCH PROCESS: Generate recommendations for ALL alerts in one loop
    var recommendations = [];
    
    for (var i = 0; i < alerts.length; i++) {
        var alert = alerts[i];
        var riskScore = alert.alert_risk_score || 7;
        var isHighRisk = riskScore >= 9;
        var alertTitle = alert.alert_title || alert.title || 'Regulatory Alert';
        
        gs.info('⚙️ Processing alert ' + (i + 1) + '/' + alerts.length + ': ' + alertTitle);
        
        // Determine impact areas based on regulation keywords
        var impactAreas = 'Legal & Compliance';
        var alertTitleLower = alertTitle.toLowerCase();
        var abstract = (alert.abstract || '').toLowerCase();
        var fullText = alertTitleLower + ' ' + abstract;
        
        if (fullText.indexOf('ai') > -1 || fullText.indexOf('algorithm') > -1 || fullText.indexOf('machine learning') > -1) {
            impactAreas = 'Legal & Compliance, AI/ML Development, IT Operations';
        } else if (fullText.indexOf('employment') > -1 || fullText.indexOf('bias') > -1 || fullText.indexOf('hiring') > -1 || fullText.indexOf('aedt') > -1) {
            impactAreas = 'HR & Employment, Legal & Compliance, Bias & Fairness';
        } else if (fullText.indexOf('data') > -1 || fullText.indexOf('privacy') > -1 || fullText.indexOf('gdpr') > -1) {
            impactAreas = 'Data Privacy, Legal & Compliance, IT Security';
        } else if (fullText.indexOf('ftc') > -1 || fullText.indexOf('marketing') > -1 || fullText.indexOf('deceptive') > -1) {
            impactAreas = 'Marketing, Legal & Compliance, Communications';
        }
        
        // Generate detailed workflow recommendations
        var workflowRecs = 'IMMEDIATE ACTIONS REQUIRED:\n\n';
        workflowRecs += '1. ASSESSMENT PHASE (Week 1-2)\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Review ' + alertTitle + ' requirements in detail\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Identify all affected systems, processes, and stakeholders\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Document current compliance gaps and deficiencies\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Estimate full remediation costs and resource needs\n\n';
        
        workflowRecs += '2. PLANNING PHASE (Week 2-3)\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Develop comprehensive implementation roadmap\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Assign clear ownership and responsibilities to teams\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Establish milestones, deliverables, and deadlines\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Secure executive approval and budget allocation\n\n';
        
        workflowRecs += '3. IMPLEMENTATION PHASE (Week 4-8)\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Update policies, procedures, and documentation\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Modify technical systems and implement controls\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Conduct training for all affected personnel\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Maintain detailed change logs and audit trails\n\n';
        
        workflowRecs += '4. VALIDATION PHASE (Week 8-10)\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Conduct internal compliance audit and testing\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Verify all requirements are properly addressed\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Address any identified gaps or deficiencies\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Prepare final compliance documentation\n\n';
        
        workflowRecs += '5. MONITORING PHASE (Ongoing)\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Establish continuous compliance monitoring\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Schedule periodic reviews and assessments\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Track regulatory updates and amendments\n';
        workflowRecs += '   • Maintain comprehensive audit trail';
        
        // Generate policy implications with budget estimates
        var policyImpl = 'EXECUTIVE SUMMARY:\n\n';
        policyImpl += 'This regulation requires immediate attention and resource allocation.\n\n';
        policyImpl += '• LEGAL RISK: Non-compliance could result in ' + (isHighRisk ? 'significant' : 'moderate') + ' penalties and legal liability\n';
        policyImpl += '• OPERATIONAL IMPACT: ' + (isHighRisk ? 'Major' : 'Moderate') + ' changes to existing business processes required\n';
        policyImpl += '• FINANCIAL IMPACT: Estimated ' + (isHighRisk ? '$50K-$200K' : '$20K-$80K') + ' for full compliance implementation\n';
        policyImpl += '• TIMELINE: ' + (isHighRisk ? 'Immediate action required within 48 hours' : 'Action required within 72 hours') + '\n';
        policyImpl += '• STAKEHOLDERS: Legal, Compliance, IT, Operations, Executive Leadership\n\n';
        policyImpl += 'RECOMMENDATION: ' + (isHighRisk ? 'Convene executive steering committee immediately' : 'Proceed with compliance officer approval') + '\n\n';
        policyImpl += 'BUDGET REQUIREMENTS:\n';
        policyImpl += '• Consulting/Legal: ' + (isHighRisk ? '$15K-$50K' : '$5K-$20K') + '\n';
        policyImpl += '• Technology Updates: ' + (isHighRisk ? '$20K-$100K' : '$10K-$40K') + '\n';
        policyImpl += '• Training & Change Management: ' + (isHighRisk ? '$5K-$20K' : '$2K-$10K') + '\n';
        policyImpl += '• Ongoing Monitoring: ' + (isHighRisk ? '$10K-$30K annually' : '$3K-$10K annually');
        
        // Build recommendation object
        var recommendation = {
            alert_sys_id: alert.sys_id,
            alert_title: alertTitle,
            alert_risk_score: riskScore,
            impact_areas: impactAreas,
            workflow_recommendations: workflowRecs,
            policy_implications: policyImpl,
            estimated_effort: isHighRisk ? 'Months (120-200 hours)' : 'Weeks (40-80 hours)',
            action_plan: JSON.stringify({
                phase1: 'Assessment & Gap Analysis (2 weeks)',
                phase2: 'Planning & Design (2-3 weeks)',
                phase3: 'Implementation & Testing (4-6 weeks)',
                phase4: 'Validation & Monitoring (Ongoing)'
            }),
            confidence_score: 85,
            requires_executive_approval: isHighRisk,
            approval_level: isHighRisk ? 'Executive' : 'Compliance Officer',
            priority: isHighRisk ? 'Critical' : 'High'
        };
        
        recommendations.push(recommendation);
        gs.info('   Generated recommendation for: ' + alertTitle);
    }
    
    gs.info('========================================');
    gs.info('BATCH COMPLETE: ' + recommendations.length + ' recommendations generated');
    gs.info('========================================');
    
    return {
        recommendations_generated: 'true',
        recommendation_count: String(recommendations.length),
        recommendations: JSON.stringify(recommendations)
    };
    
})(inputs);]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sophia.rafat</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-31 22:11:02</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>59dc917b83b472107f44e8be50da1e6a</sys_id><sys_mod_count>5</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Generate Recommendations (BATCH)</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_59dc917b83b472107f44e8be50da1e6a</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sophia.rafat</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-11-01 09:06:35</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table/><type>script</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sysauto_script"><sysauto_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><business_calendar/><condition/><conditional>false</conditional><entered_time>1970-01-01 00:00:00</entered_time><max_drift/><name>Federal Register Alerts Fetcher</name><offset/><offset_type>0</offset_type><run_as display_value="Sophia Rafat">65f7855583f032107f44e8be50da1eba</run_as><run_as_tz/><run_dayofmonth>1</run_dayofmonth><run_dayofweek>1</run_dayofweek><run_period/><run_start>2025-10-31 03:31:28</run_start><run_time>1970-01-01 00:00:00</run_time><run_type>on_demand</run_type><script><![CDATA[/**
 * Federal Register AI Ingest - AI-FOCUSED with Relevance Filtering
 */
(function () {
    gs.info('=== Federal Register AI Ingest - AI-Focused ===');

    var startDate = '2024-01-01';
    gs.info('Searching from: ' + startDate);

    // ----------------------------------------------------
    // FOCUSED AI SEARCH TERMS - More specific to AI regulations
    // ----------------------------------------------------
    var searchTerms = [
        'artificial+intelligence',
        'AI+regulation',
        'AI+governance',
        'AI+system',
        'algorithmic+accountability',
        'algorithmic+bias',
        'automated+decision+making',
        'machine+learning+model'
    ];

    var allDocs = {};
    var table = 'x_snc_ai_complia_0_regulatory_alert_2';
    var totalFetched = 0;

    // Run search for each term
    searchTerms.forEach(function(term) {
        gs.info('Searching for: ' + term.replace(/\+/g, ' '));
        
        var baseUrl = 'https://www.federalregister.gov/api/v1/documents.json';
        var params = [
            'per_page=1000',
            'order=newest',
            'conditions%5Bterm%5D=' + term,
            'conditions%5Bpublication_date%5D%5Bgte%5D=' + startDate,
            'fields%5B%5D=title',
            'fields%5B%5D=html_url',
            'fields%5B%5D=pdf_url',
            'fields%5B%5D=document_number',
            'fields%5B%5D=publication_date',
            'fields%5B%5D=effective_on',
            'fields%5B%5D=type',
            'fields%5B%5D=abstract',
            'fields%5B%5D=agencies'
        ].join('&');

        var url = baseUrl + '?' + params;

        var req = new sn_ws.RESTMessageV2();
        req.setEndpoint(url);
        req.setHttpMethod('GET');
        req.setHttpTimeout(30000);

        var res = req.execute();
        
        if (res.getStatusCode() !== 200) {
            gs.error('API failed for term: ' + term);
            return;
        }

        var body = JSON.parse(res.getBody());
        var docs = body.results || [];
        
        gs.info('  Found: ' + docs.length + ' documents (before filtering)');

        // Filter for AI relevance BEFORE deduplication
        var filtered = docs.filter(function(doc) {
            return isAIRelevant(doc);
        });
        
        gs.info('  After AI filter: ' + filtered.length + ' documents');
        totalFetched += filtered.length;

        // Deduplicate by document_number
        filtered.forEach(function(doc) {
            if (!allDocs[doc.document_number]) {
                allDocs[doc.document_number] = doc;
            }
        });
    });

    // ----------------------------------------------------
    // AI RELEVANCE FILTER
    // ----------------------------------------------------
    function isAIRelevant(doc) {
        var title = (doc.title || '').toLowerCase();
        var abstract = (doc.abstract || '').toLowerCase();
        var fullText = title + ' ' + abstract;

        // MUST contain at least one primary AI term
        var primaryAITerms = [
            'artificial intelligence',
            'machine learning',
            'neural network',
            'deep learning',
            'ai system',
            'ai model',
            'ai technology',
            'algorithmic',
            'automated decision',
            'generative ai',
            'large language model',
            'llm',
            'natural language processing',
            'computer vision',
            'predictive analytics'
        ];

        var hasPrimaryTerm = primaryAITerms.some(function(term) {
            return fullText.indexOf(term) !== -1;
        });

        if (!hasPrimaryTerm) {
            return false;
        }

        // EXCLUDE documents that are clearly not about AI regulation/governance
        var excludeTerms = [
            'visa',
            'immigration',
            'passport',
            'border patrol',
            'customs',
            'agricultural',
            'pesticide',
            'herbicide',
            'livestock',
            'fishing permit',
            'hunting license',
            'wildlife',
            'environmental impact statement',
            'mining',
            'drilling',
            'oil and gas lease',
            'timber sale',
            'grazing permit'
        ];

        var hasExcludeTerm = excludeTerms.some(function(term) {
            return fullText.indexOf(term) !== -1;
        });

        if (hasExcludeTerm) {
            // Check if it's ALSO about AI regulation
            var regulatoryTerms = [
                'regulation',
                'compliance',
                'governance',
                'oversight',
                'accountability',
                'transparency',
                'risk management',
                'safety standard',
                'ethical use',
                'bias mitigation',
                'fairness'
            ];

            var hasRegulatoryTerm = regulatoryTerms.some(function(term) {
                return fullText.indexOf(term) !== -1;
            });

            // If it has exclude terms but NO regulatory context, exclude it
            if (!hasRegulatoryTerm) {
                return false;
            }
        }

        // BOOST relevance for documents that mention regulation/governance
        var regulatoryContext = [
            'regulation',
            'rule',
            'compliance',
            'governance',
            'policy',
            'framework',
            'guideline',
            'standard',
            'requirement',
            'oversight',
            'enforcement'
        ];

        var hasRegulatoryContext = regulatoryContext.some(function(term) {
            return fullText.indexOf(term) !== -1;
        });

        // Prioritize documents with regulatory context
        // If it has AI terms AND regulatory context, it's highly relevant
        if (hasPrimaryTerm && hasRegulatoryContext) {
            return true;
        }

        // If it only has AI terms but no regulatory context,
        // check if it's from a key regulatory agency
        var keyAgencies = [
            'federal trade commission',
            'ftc',
            'department of commerce',
            'national institute of standards',
            'nist',
            'office of management and budget',
            'omb',
            'equal employment opportunity commission',
            'eeoc',
            'consumer financial protection bureau',
            'cfpb',
            'food and drug administration',
            'fda',
            'securities and exchange commission',
            'sec'
        ];

        if (doc.agencies && doc.agencies.length > 0) {
            var agencyText = doc.agencies.map(function(agency) {
                return (agency.name || agency + '').toLowerCase();
            }).join(' ');

            var isKeyAgency = keyAgencies.some(function(agency) {
                return agencyText.indexOf(agency) !== -1;
            });

            if (isKeyAgency && hasPrimaryTerm) {
                return true;
            }
        }

        // Default: if it has primary AI terms and no exclude terms, include it
        return hasPrimaryTerm;
    }

    // ----------------------------------------------------
    // Calculate relevance score for prioritization
    // ----------------------------------------------------
    function calculateRelevanceScore(doc) {
        var title = (doc.title || '').toLowerCase();
        var abstract = (doc.abstract || '').toLowerCase();
        var fullText = title + ' ' + abstract;
        var score = 0;

        // HIGH value terms
        if (fullText.indexOf('artificial intelligence') !== -1) score += 30;
        if (fullText.indexOf('machine learning') !== -1) score += 25;
        if (fullText.indexOf('algorithmic') !== -1) score += 20;

        // Regulatory context
        if (fullText.indexOf('regulation') !== -1) score += 20;
        if (fullText.indexOf('compliance') !== -1) score += 15;
        if (fullText.indexOf('governance') !== -1) score += 15;
        if (fullText.indexOf('accountability') !== -1) score += 15;

        // Document type priority
        if (doc.type === 'Rule') score += 25;
        if (doc.type === 'Proposed Rule') score += 20;
        if (doc.type === 'Notice') score += 10;

        // Title mentions AI directly
        if (title.indexOf('artificial intelligence') !== -1 || 
            title.indexOf('ai ') !== -1 || 
            title.indexOf(' ai') !== -1) {
            score += 20;
        }

        return Math.min(score, 100);
    }

    // ----------------------------------------------------
    // Process unique documents
    // ----------------------------------------------------
    var uniqueDocs = Object.keys(allDocs).map(function(key) {
        return allDocs[key];
    });

    gs.info('Total fetched (with duplicates): ' + totalFetched);
    gs.info('Unique AI-relevant documents: ' + uniqueDocs.length);

    var inserted = 0, updated = 0;

    uniqueDocs.forEach(function(doc) {
        var number = doc.document_number + '';
        var gr = new GlideRecord(table);
        gr.addQuery('document_number', number);
        gr.query();

        var isNew = !gr.next();
        
        if (isNew) {
            gr.initialize();
        }

        // Calculate relevance score
        var relevanceScore = calculateRelevanceScore(doc);

        // Populate fields
        gr.setValue('document_number', number);
        gr.setValue('alert_title', doc.title || '');
        gr.setValue('source_url', doc.html_url || '');
        gr.setValue('pdf_url', doc.pdf_url || '');
        gr.setValue('abstract', doc.abstract || '');
        gr.setValue('regulation_source', 'Federal Register');
        
        // Add relevance score if field exists
        if (gr.isValidField('relevance_score')) {
            gr.setValue('relevance_score', relevanceScore);
        }
        
        if (doc.publication_date) {
            gr.setValue('publication_date', doc.publication_date);
        }
        if (doc.effective_on) {
            gr.setValue('effective_date', doc.effective_on);
        }
        if (doc.type) {
            gr.setValue('document_type', mapDocumentType(doc.type));
        }
        
        if (doc.agencies && doc.agencies.length > 0) {
            var agencyNames = doc.agencies.map(function(agency) {
                return agency.name || agency;
            });
            gr.setValue('agencies', agencyNames.join(', '));
        }

        if (isNew) {
            gr.insert();
            inserted++;
            if (inserted <= 10) {
                gs.info('Inserted (score: ' + relevanceScore + '): ' + doc.title);
            }
        } else {
            gr.update();
            updated++;
        }
    });

    gs.info('=== COMPLETE ===');
    gs.info('Unique AI-relevant documents found: ' + uniqueDocs.length);
    gs.info('Inserted: ' + inserted);
    gs.info('Updated: ' + updated);

    function mapDocumentType(apiType) {
        var typeMap = {
            'Rule': 'Final Rule',
            'Proposed Rule': 'Proposed Rule',
            'Notice': 'Notice',
            'Presidential Document': 'Notice',
            'Sunshine Act Document': 'Notice'
        };
        return typeMap[apiType] || apiType;
    }

})();]]></script><sys_class_name>sysauto_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>sophia.rafat</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-31 03:32:00</sys_created_on><sys_id>d19c95e3837872107f44e8be50da1e9f</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Federal Register Alerts Fetcher</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sysauto_script_d19c95e3837872107f44e8be50da1e9f</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sophia.rafat</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-31 03:44:15</sys_updated_on><time_zone/><upgrade_safe>false</upgrade_safe></sysauto_script></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sn_aia_tool"><sn_aia_tool action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description>Get audit data from the dataset field</description><input_schema>[{"name":"bias_audit_sys_id","description":""},{"name":"crudInputs","description":"CRUD Input Variables. These are already pre-defined. Under no circumstances should you prompt the user for this information or attempt to change these values."}]</input_schema><name>Get Bias Audit Data</name><record_type>custom</record_type><script><![CDATA[(function(inputs) {
    // only string inputs are allowed 
    // return outputs object where the keys in it are understandable by LLM    
    // lookup script

    // parses expression containing {{variables}}
    function parseQuery(expression, inputs) {
        if (!expression) return "";
        return expression.replace(/{{\s*(\w+)\s*}}/g, function(match, variableName) {
            if (inputs && inputs.hasOwnProperty(variableName)) {
                return inputs[variableName];
            }
            return "";
        });

    }

    function getTypedValue(gr, table, field) {
        var fieldValue = gr.getValue(field.id);
        if (field.type === "choice") {
            var choiceGR = new GlideRecordSecure("sys_choice");
            choiceGR.addQuery("name", table);
            choiceGR.addQuery("element", field.id);
            choiceGR.addQuery("value", fieldValue);
            choiceGR.query();
            if (choiceGR.next()) {
                return choiceGR.getValue('label');
            }
        } else if (field.referenceTable) {
            var refName = field.referenceTableDefaultField;
            var refGR = new GlideRecordSecure(field.referenceTable);
            refGR.addQuery("sys_id", fieldValue);
            refGR.query();
            if (refName && refGR.next()) {
                return refGR.getValue(refName);
            }
        }
        return fieldValue;
    }

    var table = inputs.crudInputs.table.value;
    var tableName = inputs.crudInputs.table.displayValue;
    var query = parseQuery(inputs.crudInputs.query, inputs);
    var sortType = inputs.crudInputs.sortType;
    var orderBy = inputs.crudInputs.orderBy;
    var limit = inputs.crudInputs.limit || 5;
    var fields = inputs.crudInputs.returnFields || [];

    var results = [];
    var protectedRecords = 0;
    var gr = new GlideRecordSecure(table);
    if (query) {
        gr.addEncodedQuery(query);
    }
    if (orderBy && sortType === 'a_to_z') {
        gr.orderBy(orderBy);
    } else if (orderBy && sortType !== 'a_to_z') {
        gr.orderByDesc(orderBy);
    }

    gr.setLimit(limit);
    gr.query();
    while (gr.next()) {
        var fieldObj = {};
        if (gr.canRead()) {
            fields.forEach(function(field) {
                if (gr.canRead(field.id)) {
                    fieldObj[field.id] = getTypedValue(gr, table, field);
                } else {
                    // number of fields that cannot be read for each record
                    if (fieldObj["protectedFields"] >= 1) {
                        fieldObj["protectedFields"]++;
                    } else {
                        fieldObj["protectedFields"] = 1;
                    }
                }
            });
        } else {
            protectedRecords++;
        }
        results.push(fieldObj);
    }
    var recordCount = results.length;
    var total = recordCount + protectedRecords;
    var message = gs.getMessage("{0} out of {1} records returned from the {2} table.",
        [recordCount.toString(), total.toString(), tableName]);

    return {
        "records": results,
        "message": message,
        "status": "success"
    };
})(inputs);]]></script><sys_class_name>sn_aia_tool</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>frants.k</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-25 22:44:58</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>330ba2f983b432107f44e8be50da1e0b</sys_id><sys_mod_count>2</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Get Bias Audit Data</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sn_aia_tool_330ba2f983b432107f44e8be50da1e0b</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>sophia.rafat</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-26 01:31:10</sys_updated_on><target_document/><target_document_table/><type>crud</type></sn_aia_tool></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ws_operation"><sys_ws_operation action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><consumes>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</consumes><consumes_customized>false</consumes_customized><default_operation_uri/><enforce_acl>cf9d01d3e73003009d6247e603f6a990</enforce_acl><http_method>POST</http_method><name>Update Training Status</name><operation_script><![CDATA[(function process(/*RESTAPIRequest*/ request, /*RESTAPIResponse*/ response) {
    try {
        var body = request.body.data;

        if (!body || !body.enrollmentID) {
            response.setStatus(400);
            return { error: "Missing required field: enrollmentID" };
        }

        var gr = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_training_enrollments');
        gr.addQuery('number', body.enrollmentID);
        gr.query();

		var gr2 = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_ai_access_employee');
		gr2.addQuery('number', body.employeeID);
        gr2.query();

		var gr3 = new GlideRecord('x_snc_ai_complia_0_evidence_pack');
		gr3.addQuery('number', body.evidenceID);
        gr3.query();

        if (gr.next() && gr2.next() && gr3.next()) {
			var evidenceRecordSysId = gr3.getUniqueValue();
			// Training Enrollments 
            gr.setValue('completion_date', new GlideDateTime());
            gr.setValue('training_results', body.results || '');
			gr.setValue('evidence', evidenceRecordSysId);
			gr.setValue('status', 'completed');
            gr.update();

			// AI Access Employee
			gr2.setValue('needs_ai_training', false);
			gr2.update();

			// Evidence Pack
			gr3.setValue('digital_signature', body.signature);
			gr3.setValue('signed_by', body.agent);
			gr3.setValue('hashed_data', body.results || '');
			gr3.update();
			
            response.setStatus(200);
            return {
                message: "Enrollment updated successfully",
                enrollmentID: body.enrollmentID
            };
        } else {
            response.setStatus(404);
            return { error: "Enrollment not found" };
        }
    } catch (e) {
        gs.error("Scripted REST API error: " + e.message);
        response.setStatus(500);
        return { error: "Internal server error" };
    }
})(request, response);
]]></operation_script><operation_uri>/api/x_snc_ai_complia_0/ai_literacy/updatetrainingstatus</operation_uri><produces>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</produces><produces_customized>false</produces_customized><relative_path>/updatetrainingstatus</relative_path><request_example/><requires_acl_authorization>true</requires_acl_authorization><requires_authentication>true</requires_authentication><requires_snc_internal_role>true</requires_snc_internal_role><short_description/><sys_class_name>sys_ws_operation</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2025-10-19 16:10:34</sys_created_on><sys_id>acefc6bb836032107f44e8be50da1ea7</sys_id><sys_mod_count>9</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Update Training Status</sys_name><sys_package display_value="AI Compliance Command Center" source="x_snc_ai_complia_0">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="AI Compliance Command Center">7a91febe83a032107f44e8be50da1e4b</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ws_operation_acefc6bb836032107f44e8be50da1ea7</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2025-10-21 03:10:58</sys_updated_on><web_service_definition display_value="AI Literacy">fb8d0a37836032107f44e8be50da1ed9</web_service_definition><web_service_version/></sys_ws_operation></record_update>
